(278, 'Zephirine Drouhin Climbing Rose Starter Plant: Thornless, Fragrant Deep Pink Flowers', 'zephirine-drouhin-climbing-rose-starter-plant-thornless-fragrant-deep-pink-flowers', 'ETSY-0006', 'simple', 9, NULL, 'Roses', 27.90, NULL, 16.74, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/009043/6017606736/il_fullxfull.6017606736_2qf6.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live starter plant that is 3\" - 6\" tall and growing quickly in a quart pot! This is another beautiful climbing Rose that is thornless! In Spring, it starts blooming with highly fragrant flowers that are deep rose pink! It also blooms continuously through Summer and well into Fall! It is mostly used as a climber, but it can also be grown as a shrub too!!\n\nCommon Name: \'Zephirine Drouhin\' Climbing Rose or Bourbon Rose\nBotanical Name: Rosa\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: Spring through Fall\nSunlight: Full sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 4\' to 12\' tall and 3\' to 6\' wide\nBloom Color: Deep rose pink\nEvergreen or Deciduous: Deciduous', '1 live starter plant that is 3\" - 6\" tall and growing quickly in a quart pot! This is another beautiful climbing Rose that is thornless! In Spring, it starts blooming with highly fragrant flowers that are deep rose pink!...', '[\"Continuous Blooms\",\"Reblooming Rose\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Cut Flowers\",\"Highly Fragrant\",\"Bourbon Rose\",\"Repeat Bloomer\",\"Heirloom Rose\",\"Large Flowers\",\"Flowering Hedge\",\"Thornless Rose\",\"Medium Climber\",\"Fast Growing\"]', 1, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 6, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:08:59', '2026-06-24 16:08:59'),
(279, 'Japanese Maple \'Frosted Purple\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Reticulated Reddish Purple Leaves---Beautiful!!', 'japanese-maple-frosted-purple-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-reticulated-reddish-purple-leaves-beautiful', 'ETSY-0007', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/63e076/6964416718/il_fullxfull.6964416718_ql9o.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 plant that is 6\"- 8\" tall. This grafted variety has a lot to offer! It stands out within the \"Ghost series\" style of maples for its highly vibrant, almost glowing spring coloration and intense structural definition. To maintain the brilliant \"frosted\" look without getting leaf scorch, give \'Frosted Purple\' morning sun and afternoon shade. Variegated and Ghost-type maples perform best when protected from the harsh, direct afternoon heat.\n\nFoliage & Reticulation: In the spring, the serrated, jagged leaves emerge a very bright, light pink-purple or deep pink with stark, dark purple veins. This prominent patterning—where the veins contrast sharply against the rest of the leaf blade—is known as reticulation.  \n\nSummer & Fall Shifts: As summer progresses, the color mellows slightly, showing cream-white or frosted pink variegation over the purple-green base, though its reticulated veins hold strong. In autumn, it transitions to a rich, fiery red or red-purple.  \n\nSize & Growth Habit: It is an upright, sculptural, and somewhat columnar grower. It reaches about 6 to 8 feet tall and 4 to 6 feet wide in its first 10 years, eventually maxing out around 10 to 12 feet, making it excellent for smaller gardens or container planting.  \n\nSoil: Requires well-draining, slightly acidic soil. Like most Japanese maples, it is highly sensitive to \"wet feet\" (saturated, soggy soil), which can quickly lead to root rot.\n\nCommon Name: \'Frosted Purple\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Morning sun/Afternoon shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 6\'-8\' tall and 4\'-6\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 plant that is 6\"- 8\" tall.', '[\"Japanese Maples\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Reticulated Leaves\",\"Vibrant Color\",\"Brilliant Fall Color\",\"Woodland Garden\",\"Jagged Edge Leaves\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Asian Garden\",\"Upright Growth Habit\",\"Ornamental Tree\",\"Cottage Garden\"]', 1, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:08:59', '2026-06-24 16:08:59'),
(280, 'Korean Lilac \'Miss Kim\' Syringa patula Live Plant Flowering Shrub Fragrant Lavender Blue Flowers---Gorgeous!!', 'korean-lilac-miss-kim-syringa-patula-live-plant-flowering-shrub-fragrant-lavender-blue-flowers-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0008', 'simple', 17, NULL, 'Lilacs', 22.45, NULL, 13.47, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/d3541d/4832973855/il_fullxfull.4832973855_1hxa.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n*** WE DO NOT SHIP TO PO BOXES***\nSecond photo is a representation of the plant you will receive.\nThis listing is for 1 semi-dormant live plant that is 6\"- 8\" tall. Beautiful flowers and lots of fragrance? Yes please!! In Spring, this wonderful shrub  has deep purple buds that open up into lavender blue flower clusters that are highly fragrant! In Fall, the foliage is burgundy tinged to add more to its charm! Great when planted in groups or as a specimen plant!\n\nCommon Name: \'Miss Kim\' Korean Lilac\nBotanical Name: Syringa patula\nHardiness Zones: 4 - 8\nBloom Time: Spring\nSunlight: Full sun/part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 6\' to 8\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: Lavender blue\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 semi-dormant live plant that is 6\"- 8\" tall.', '[\"Low Maintenance\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Spring Flowers\",\"Highly Fragrant\",\"Attracts Butterflies\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Fall Color\",\"Cut Flowers\",\"Pollinator Plant\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Attract Hummingbirds\",\"Hedge Plant\",\"Specimen Planting\"]', 1, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 3, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:08:59', '2026-06-24 16:08:59'),
(281, 'Japanese Flowering Quince \'Cameo\' Shrub: Coral Pink Flowers, Thornless Ornamental Plant', 'japanese-flowering-quince-cameo-shrub-coral-pink-flowers-thornless-ornamental-plant', 'ETSY-0009', 'simple', 3, NULL, 'Perennials', 24.85, NULL, 14.91, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/b23583/4865924868/il_fullxfull.4865924868_3dff.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\nWE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1  live plant that is 6\"- 10\" tall. This beautiful variety of flowering Quince grows in a compact shape and is absolutely gorgeous in Spring! It has tons of semi-double flower clusters that are coral pink in color. The flowers will turn into fragrant greenish yellow fruit. The fruit is edible, but it\'s best to use them in jelly or preserves...they are bitter if eaten directly from the shrub. The branches are thornless and it needs very little if any pruning! These plants work great as an accent plant or as a low hedge/border!!\n\nCommon Name: \'Cameo\' Flowering Quince\nBotanical Name: Chaenomeles x superba\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: Spring\nSunlight: Full sun/part sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 4\' to 5\' tall wide\nBloom Color: Coral pink\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live plant that is 6\"- 10\" tall.', '[\"Low Maintenance\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Spring Flowers\",\"Edible Fruit\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Urban Garden\",\"Low Hedge\",\"Drought Tolerant\",\"Flowering Hedge\",\"Pollinator Plant\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Specimen Plant\",\"Border Plant\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:08:59', '2026-06-24 16:08:59'),
