(284, 'Knockout Rose \'Orange Glow\' Starter Plant Semi-Double Flowers---Beautiful!!', 'knockout-rose-orange-glow-starter-plant-semi-double-flowers-beautiful', 'ETSY-0012', 'simple', 9, NULL, 'Roses', 25.90, NULL, 15.54, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/977607/8001586156/il_fullxfull.8001586156_tgy5.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live starter plant that is 3\" - 6\" tall and growing quickly in a quart pot! This variety is a highly disease-resistant, low maintenance shrub rose. It has double-petaled orange flowers that bloom continuously from spring until frost and don\'t require deadheading!!\n\nCommon Name: \'Orange Glow\'  Knockout Rose\nBotanical Name: Rosa \'Radslam\' PP 35,826\nHardiness Zones: 4 - 10\nBloom Time: Spring, Summer, Fall\nSunlight: Full sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 3\' to 4\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: Orange suffused with coral, yellow, and pink\nEvergreen or Deciduous: Deciduous', '1 live starter plant that is 3\" - 6\" tall and growing quickly in a quart pot! This variety is a highly disease-resistant, low maintenance shrub rose.', '[\"Shrub Rose\",\"Long Bloom Time\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Cut Flowers\",\"Container Garden\",\"Garden Border\",\"Flowering Hedge\",\"Low Hedge\",\"Bushy Rose\",\"Fast Growing\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Self Deadheading\",\"Disease Resistant\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 4, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:00', '2026-06-24 16:09:00'),
(285, 'Hardy Hibiscus moscheutos \'Luna Red\' Perennial Live Plant Huge Red Flowers--Gorgeous!!', 'hardy-hibiscus-moscheutos-luna-red-perennial-live-plant-huge-red-flowers-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0013', 'simple', 3, NULL, 'Perennials', 24.75, NULL, 14.85, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/5e1f88/4923228824/il_fullxfull.4923228824_8lwc.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live very large plant that is 8\"- 12\" tall and growing! This beautiful variety comes back year after year and produce large red flowers in Summer and Fall...did I say the flowers are huge? The plant will die back to the ground in Winter and can be a little slow to make an appearance in Spring, but it\'s well worth the wait! Make your landscape the talk of the neighborhood with these beauties!\n\n\nCommon Name: \'Luna Red\' Hardy Hibiscus\nBotanical Name: Hibiscus moscheutos\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: Summer to Fall\nSunlight: Full sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 2\' to 3\' tall and 1\' to 2\' wide\nBloom Color: Red\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous....dies back to the ground in Winter', '1 live very large plant that is 8\"- 12\" tall and growing! This beautiful variety comes back year after year and produce large red flowers in Summer and Fall.', '[\"Red Flower\",\"Large Flower\",\"Easy Care\",\"Urban Garden\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Pollinator Plant\",\"Attracts Butterflies\",\"Tropical Look\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Container Plant\",\"Border Plant\",\"Specimen Plant\",\"Hummingbirds Love\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 6, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:01', '2026-06-24 16:09:01'),
(286, 'Hardy Hibiscus moscheutos \'Luna Pink Swirl\' Shrubby Perennial Live Plant Huge Pink & White Flowers--Gorgeous!!', 'hardy-hibiscus-moscheutos-luna-pink-swirl-shrubby-perennial-live-plant-huge-pink-white-flowers-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0014', 'simple', 3, NULL, 'Perennials', 24.75, NULL, 14.85, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/51fad8/3927417856/il_fullxfull.3927417856_9ab5.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA!!\n***WE DO NOT SHIP TO PO BOXES***\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live plant that is 6\"- 8\" tall and growing! This beautiful variety comes back year after year and produce large pink flowers with white streaks in Summer and Fall...did I say the flowers are huge? The flowers measure a whopping 8\" across! The plant will die back to the ground in Winter and can be a little slow to make an appearance in Spring, but it\'s well worth the wait! Make your landscape the talk of the neighborhood with these beauties!\n\nCommon Name: \'Luna Pink Swirl\' Hardy Hibiscus\nBotanical Name: Hibiscus moscheutos\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: Summer to Fall\nSunlight: Full sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 2\' to 3\' tall and 2\' to 3\' wide\nBloom Color: Pink with white streaks\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous....dies back to the ground in Winter', '1 live plant that is 6\"- 8\" tall and growing! This beautiful variety comes back year after year and produce large pink flowers with white streaks in Summer and Fall.', '[\"Large Flower\",\"Easy Care\",\"Urban Garden\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Pollinator Plant\",\"Attracts Butterflies\",\"Tropical Look\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Container Plant\",\"Border Plant\",\"Pond Border\",\"Hummingbirds Love\",\"Specimen Plant\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 6, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:01', '2026-06-24 16:09:01'),
(287, 'Japanese Maple \'Inaba Shidare\' Acer palmatum dissectum Live High Graft Tree Dwarf Red Laceleaf Weeping---Stunning!!', 'japanese-maple-inaba-shidare-acer-palmatum-dissectum-live-high-graft-tree-dwarf-red-laceleaf-weeping-stunning', 'ETSY-0015', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/65ef91/5871687903/il_fullxfull.5871687903_bwb5.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live high grafted tree that is 8\"- 10\" tall. Another beautiful dwarf red laceleaf weeping cultivar! This cultivar is widely considered one of the best cascading, laceleaf Japanese maples you can grow. The name translates beautifully from Japanese as \"leaves like a cascading rice tassel,\" which perfectly describes its weeping habit. What makes this specific cultivar stand out from other red dissectums (like \'Tamukeyama\' or \'Crimson Queen\') is its exceptional color retention and slightly more robust, upright-then-weeping growth pattern.\n\nFoliage: It features large, deeply divided, intricate lace-like leaves. The color emerges as a brilliant, deep purple-red in the spring.\n\nSummer Heat Resistance: While many red Japanese maples \"green out\" or scorch during hot summer months, \'Inaba shidare\' holds onto its dark burgundy-purple hues remarkably well, even in full sun.\n\nAutumn Show: In the fall, the dark canopy shifts dramatically into a fiery, bright crimson-red.\n\nGrowth Habit: It forms a cascading mound that tends to grow slightly taller and faster than other weeping varieties, giving it a strong architectural presence in landscapes or large containers.\n\nMature Size: 6 to 10 feet tall and 8 to 12 feet wide\nSun Exposure: Full sun to partial shade (performs best with afternoon shade in hot climates)\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well-drained, slightly acidic soil; intolerant of wet feet\n\nCommon Name: \'Inaba Shidare\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum dissectum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Full sun/part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 6\' to 10\' tall and 8\' to 12\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live high grafted tree that is 8\"- 10\" tall.', '[\"Japanese Maple\",\"Ornamental Tree\",\"Fine Textured Leaf\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Fall Color\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Small Spaces\",\"Container Tree\",\"Bonsai Tree\",\"Graceful Form\",\"Patio Plant\",\"Courtyard Garden\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:01', '2026-06-24 16:09:01'),
(288, 'Japanese Flowering Quince \'Texas Scarlet\' Chaenomeles x Superba Live Plant Scarlet Red Flowers---Stunning!!', 'japanese-flowering-quince-texas-scarlet-chaenomeles-x-superba-live-plant-scarlet-red-flowers-stunning', 'ETSY-0016', 'simple', 3, NULL, 'Perennials', 24.85, NULL, 14.91, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/3c36da/5779350311/il_fullxfull.5779350311_pipu.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n***WE DO NOT SHIP TO PO BOXES***\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live plant that is 6\" - 10\" tall. This beautiful shrub explodes with scarlet red flowers in early Spring before the leaves appear! It has glossy green leaves and the flowers turn into fragrant greenish yellow fruits that are edible, but not directly off the plant. They are much better used in jelly and preserves. Just be careful when you pick the fruit since this shrub is thorny!!\n\nCommon Name: \'Texas Scarlet\' Flowering Quince\nBotanical Name: Chaenomeles x superba\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: Spring\nSunlight: Full sun/part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 3\' to 4\' tall and 4\' to 5\' wide\nBloom Color: Red\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live plant that is 6\" - 10\" tall.', '[\"Cottage Garden\",\"Spring Flowers\",\"Edible Fruit\",\"Brilliant Color\",\"Attracts Birds\",\"Wildlife Habitat\",\"Informal Garden\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Attracts Pollinators\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Informal Hedge\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Specimen Plant\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 8, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:01', '2026-06-24 16:09:01'),
