(294, 'Arborose Florentina Climbing Rose Starter Plant: Fragrant Bright Red Flowers', 'arborose-florentina-climbing-rose-starter-plant-fragrant-bright-red-flowers', 'ETSY-0022', 'simple', 9, NULL, 'Roses', 27.90, NULL, 16.74, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/096eed/8000983218/il_fullxfull.8000983218_smqy.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live starter plant that is 3\" - 6\" tall and growing quickly in a quart pot! This is another beautiful climbing Rose that is very robust and winter-hardy! In Spring, it starts blooming with moderately fragrant flowers that are bright red! It also blooms continuously through Summer and well into Fall! It is mostly used as a climbing arbors, trellis, fences and pergolas. \n\nCommon Name: \'Arborose Florentina\' Climbing Rose\nBotanical Name: Rosa \'KORtrameilo\' PP 24,196\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: Spring through Fall\nSunlight: Full sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 7\' tall and 3\' to 4\' wide\nBloom Color: Bright red\nEvergreen or Deciduous: Deciduous', '1 live starter plant that is 3\" - 6\" tall and growing quickly in a quart pot! This is another beautiful climbing Rose that is very robust and winter-hardy! In Spring, it starts blooming with moderately fragrant flowers t...', '[\"Continuous Blooms\",\"Reblooming Rose\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Cut Flowers\",\"Repeat Bloomer\",\"Heirloom Rose\",\"Large Flowers\",\"Flowering Hedge\",\"Medium Climber\",\"Fast Growing\",\"Fragrant\",\"Arbor Rose\",\"Full Sun\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 4, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:03', '2026-06-24 16:09:03'),
(295, 'Fig \"Brown Turkey\" Ficus carica Live Plant Perennial Tree Self Pollinating Produces Fruit---Yummy!!', 'fig-brown-turkey-ficus-carica-live-plant-perennial-tree-self-pollinating-produces-fruit-yummy', 'ETSY-0023', 'simple', 11, NULL, 'Fruit Trees & Shrubs', 22.95, NULL, 13.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/393610/8100726769/il_fullxfull.8100726769_iwj2.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live plant that is 6\"-8\" tall. If you are looking for a Fig that will grow in a colder area, this is the one!! Even better, it is self-pollinating so you don\'t need more than one!! It has deep green unique 3 lobed leaves that look great and you can start enjoying a small crop of fruit the first year! In Summer, the fruit starts to ripen and is deep purple which adds to its visual interest! These are great to use as a specimen plant and can also be used in containers!!\n\nCommon Name: \"Brown Turkey\" Fig\nBotanical Name: Ficus carica\nHardiness Zones: 6 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Full sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 20\' to 30\' tall wide\nBloom Color: Edible Fruit\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live plant that is 6\"-8\" tall.', '[\"Low Maintenance\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Edible\",\"Unique\",\"Self Pollinating\",\"Cold Hardy\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Specimen Plant\",\"Container Plant\",\"Disease Resistant\",\"Pest Resistant\",\"Drought Tolerant\",\"Sweet Fruit\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 5, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:03', '2026-06-24 16:09:03'),
(296, 'Japanese Fantail (Dragon Tail) Willow Live Starter Plant - Hedge, Windbreak, Shade---Fast Growing!!', 'japanese-fantail-dragon-tail-willow-live-starter-plant-hedge-windbreak-shade-fast-growing', 'ETSY-0024', 'simple', 12, NULL, 'Willows', 16.85, NULL, 10.11, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/f425ff/7905077705/il_fullxfull.7905077705_ixgw.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII AND NEVADA!!\n***WE DO NOT SHIP TO PO BOXES***\nSecond picture is a representation of the plant you will receive.\n\nThis listing is for 1 live starter plant that is 4\"- 6\" tall and multi-branched. This beautiful variety is one the fastest growing of all the Willows with a unique flattened, fasciated, and curved reddish-purple branches. Fuzzy gray catkins on previous year\'s growth. They can grow 6\' to 10\' per year...WOW!! If you are looking for a plant that will provide shade, protection and privacy than this is definitely the one for you!!\n\n\nCommon Name: Japanese Fantail (Dragon Tail) Willow\nBotanical Name: Salix undensis \'Sekka\'\nHardiness Zones: 4 - 7\nBloom Time: Spring\nSunlight: Full sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 10\' to 15\' tall and 10\' to 15\' wide\nBloom Color: Gray Catkin\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live starter plant that is 4\"- 6\" tall and multi-branched.', '[\"Low Maintenance\",\"Privacy\",\"Windbreak\",\"Fast Growing\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Disease Resistant\",\"Pest Resistant\",\"Sound Barrier\",\"Control Soil Erosion\",\"Dense Growth\",\"Block Ugly Views\",\"Non Invasive\",\"Starter Plant\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 12, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:04', '2026-06-24 16:09:04');
