(297, 'Japanese Maple \'Bihou\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Rare Yellow Bark Year Round Color---Beautiful!!', 'japanese-maple-bihou-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-rare-yellow-bark-year-round-color-beautiful', 'ETSY-0025', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/786639/7046281808/il_fullxfull.7046281808_nvfw.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 6\"- 8\" tall. This is a gorgeous yellow bark cultivar is a spectacular, prized cultivar loved primarily for its striking, architectural winter interest. Its name fittingly translates from Japanese to English as \"beautiful mountain range\" or \"precious jewel.\"\nWhile classic coral-bark maples like \'Sango kaku\' dominate gardens with bright red winter branches, \'Bihou\' offers a luminous alternative with its vivid, almost glowing bark.\n\nThe Bark: During the spring and summer, the bark is a pleasant, clean green-gold. As temperatures drop in autumn and winter, the magic happens: the young branches and twigs transform into an intense, glowing apricot-yellow to golden-orange, sometimes blushing with soft pink highlights on the sides exposed to direct sunlight.\n\nThe Foliage: In spring, the chartreuse leaves emerge with subtle reddish-orange margins. They mature into a bright, clean medium green for the summer months.\n\nFall Color: In autumn, the foliage puts on a final show, turning brilliant shades of yellow, gold, and deep orange, perfectly complementing the changing color of the wood beneath.\n\nThis tree is a relatively fast grower when young, establishing an upright, vase-shaped structure. Over time, it softens into a beautifully rounded, dense small tree.\n\nHeight: 10 to 14 feet at maturity.\n\nWidth: 6 to 10 feet wide.\n\nSuitability: Its compact, upright silhouette makes it an exceptional choice for smaller urban gardens, focal entryways, or as a high-contrast understory tree.\n\nSunlight: It performs best in dappled shade or morning sun with afternoon protection. While full morning sun intensifies the winter bark coloration, harsh, intense afternoon sun can scorch its bright leaves.\n\nSoil: Like most Japanese maples, it demands well-draining, moist, and acidic soil rich in organic matter. It will not tolerate heavy, soggy clay (\"wet feet\").\n\nCommon Name: \'Bihou\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum \nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Morning Sun/Afternoon Shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 10\' to 14\' tall and 6\' to 10\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 6\"- 8\" tall.', '[\"Japanese Maples\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Brilliant Fall Color\",\"Year Round Color\",\"Unique Bark Color\",\"Contrasting Colors\",\"Rare Tree\",\"Hard To Find Tree\",\"Woodland Garden\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Asian Garden\",\"Winter Color\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:04', '2026-06-24 16:09:04'),
(298, 'Fashion Azalea Starter Plant – Salmon-Orange to Red Blooms, Semi-Evergreen Shrub', 'fashion-azalea-starter-plant-salmon-orange-to-red-blooms-semi-evergreen-shrub', 'ETSY-0026', 'simple', 15, NULL, 'Evergreen Shrubs', 17.25, NULL, 10.35, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/474ce9/7929884341/il_fullxfull.7929884341_mjme.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n\nThis listing is for 1 live starter plant that is 3\"- 4\" tall and multi-branched. This beautiful plant has so much to offer! It is an semi-evergreen (evergreen zone 8 to 10) ornamental shrub has medium to dark green leaves. In Spring, it explodes with gorgeous flowers that are salmon-orange to red that really stands out! It has an upright growth habit with a rounded shape and makes a great hedge! \n\nCommon Name: \"Fashion\" Azalea\nBotanical Name: Azalea x\nHardiness Zones: 6 - 10\nBloom Time: Spring, Summer\nSunlight: Morning sun and afternoon shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 2\' to 3\' tall and 3\' to 4\' wide\nBloom Color: Salmon-orange to Red\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Semi-Evergreen', '1 live starter plant that is 3\"- 4\" tall and multi-branched.', '[\"Low Maintenance\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Summer Flowers\",\"Compact\",\"Hedge\",\"Specimen\",\"Rebloomer\",\"Heat Resistant\",\"Drought Resistant\",\"Disease Resistant\",\"Fast Growing\",\"Bi-Color Flowers\",\"Vibrant Color\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:04', '2026-06-24 16:09:04'),
(299, 'Japanese Maple \'Geisha Gone Wild\' Acer palmatum Live Tree Grafted Variegated Pink & Red Leaves---Stunning!!', 'japanese-maple-geisha-gone-wild-acer-palmatum-live-tree-grafted-variegated-pink-red-leaves-stunning', 'ETSY-0027', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/198d97/5418643883/il_fullxfull.5418643883_hyux.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live plant that is 8\" - 10\" tall. This grafted variegated variety is a real beauty and is one of the most striking, color-shifting dwarf trees you can add to a garden. It is a sport (a naturally occurring genetic mutation) of the older cultivar \'Geisha\', but it boasts much more vigorous growth and intense, stable variegation.\nWhat makes this tree so sought after is its dramatic, \"wild\" color transformation throughout the year:\nSpring: The showstopper season. Leaves emerge with a bright, hot pink and magenta border surrounding a purplish-green center. The contrast is incredibly vivid.\nSummer: The pink edges soften into a creamy white or pastel pink variegation, while the center of the leaf shifts to a deeper green, occasionally splashed with white.\nAutumn: The tree wraps up the growing season with a brilliant display of orange-to-purple-red fire.\n\nThis is a slower-growing, compact dwarf tree with an upright, bushy habit.\nHeight: Expect it to reach about 6 feet tall and 4 feet wide over a 10-year period.\nContainers: Because of its small stature and controlled growth, it is a perfect candidate for large patio containers or small courtyard gardens.\n\nLight: Morning sun with afternoon shade is highly recommended. The delicate pink and white variegated edges are susceptible to leaf scorch if exposed to intense, direct afternoon sunlight. However, too much deep shade will cause the vibrant colors to fade to a dull green.\nSoil: Like most Japanese maples, it thrives in moist, well-draining, slightly acidic soil. It hates having \"wet feet\" (waterlogged roots), so ensure proper drainage whether it is in the ground or a pot.\n\nCommon Name: \'Geisha Gone Wild\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 5\'-6\' tall and 3\'-4\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live plant that is 8\" - 10\" tall.', '[\"Variegated Foliage\",\"Unique Leaf Color\",\"Dramatic Color\",\"Fall Color\",\"Small Tree\",\"Small Space\",\"Dwarf Tree\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Showy Leaves\",\"Container Tree\",\"Patio Garden\",\"City Garden\",\"Japanese Garden\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 3, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:04', '2026-06-24 16:09:04'),
(300, 'Rose Creek Abelia x grandiflora Live Starter Plant Flowering Shrub White Flowers---Gorgeous!!', 'rose-creek-abelia-x-grandiflora-live-starter-plant-flowering-shrub-white-flowers-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0028', 'simple', 3, NULL, 'Perennials', 16.85, NULL, 10.11, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/09233e/8018250009/il_fullxfull.8018250009_g5s1.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n***WE DO NOT SHIP TO PO BOXES***\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF WHAT YOU WILL RECEIVE!!\n\nThis listing is for 1 live starter plant that is 3\"- 5\" tall, growing in a 2 1/2\" pot. This beautiful variety has glossy green leaves, is semi-evergreen and has gorgeous bell-shaped slightly fragrant white flowers in Summer! The flowering continues on its arching branches into Fall to really make a statement! Easy to grow and attracts all of your favorite pollinators too!!\n\nCommon Name: \'Rose Creekr\' Abelia\nBotanical Name: Abelia x grandiflora\nHardiness Zones: 6 - 9\nBloom Time: Summer to Fall\nSunlight: Full sun/part sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 3\' to 4\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: White\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Semi-evergreen', '1 live starter plant that is 3\"- 5\" tall, growing in a 2 1/2\" pot.', '[\"Low Maintenance\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Summer Flowers\",\"Fall Flowers\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Border Planting\",\"Informal Hedge\",\"Arching Branches\",\"Attracts Pollinators\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Hummingbirds Love\",\"Dramatic Fall Color\",\"Starter Plant\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 6, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:04', '2026-06-24 16:09:04'),
(301, 'Japanese Maple \'Miss Piggy\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Unique Branch Growth---Hard To Find!!', 'japanese-maple-miss-piggy-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-unique-branch-growth-hard-to-find', 'ETSY-0029', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/aa0ca4/7216686230/il_fullxfull.7216686230_etxl.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 8\" - 12\" tall. This is a beautiful cultivar that is highly desirable and hard to find!! This is a highly unique, dwarf deciduous tree prized by collectors for its compact size, multi-layered texture, and distinct color shifts. Despite the glamorous Muppet namesake, this cultivar is actually a tough, dense little grower that is perfect for small gardens, containers, or bonsai. Thanks to its miniature growth rate, \'Miss Piggy\' thrives long-term in pots. Just ensure the container has excellent drainage holes and use a high-quality, aerated potting mix.\n\nGrowth Habit & Size: It is a true dwarf variety. It typically grows into a tight, dense, rounded globose shrub shape, reaching only about 3 to 4 feet tall and wide over 10 years.\n\nFoliage Texture: The leaves are heavily layered and tightly clustered on short stems, giving the plant a distinctly crinkled, bunched, or tufted appearance.\n\nSpring: Leaves emerge a vibrant lime or light chartreuse green, often supported by striking bright red petioles (leaf stems). The tips of the leaves can feature subtle pink or reddish-orange margins.\n\nSummer: The foliage matures into a deeper, rich forest green, maintaining its dense structure.\n\nAutumn: It puts on a dramatic finale with fall colors ranging from bright orange to fiery, vivid reds.\n\nSunlight: Dappled shade to morning sun with afternoon protection. Hot, direct afternoon sun can scorch its delicate dwarf leaves.\nSoil: Moist, rich, organic, and well-draining. Like most Japanese maples, it hates sitting in soggy soil, which can cause root rot.\nWatering: Regular watering, especially during hot summer stretches. Mulching around the base helps retain consistent soil moisture.\n\nCommon Name: \'Miss Piggy\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum dissectum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Part sun/part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 3\' to 4\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 8\" - 12\" tall.', '[\"Japanese Maple\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Rare Tree\",\"Hard To Find\",\"Unique Branches\",\"Grafted Tree\",\"Fasciated Branches\",\"Specimen Tree\",\"Small Garden Space\",\"Brilliant Fall Color\",\"Eye Catching Leaves\",\"Slow Grower\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 2, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:05', '2026-06-24 16:09:05'),
(302, 'Astilbe japonica \'Montgomery\' Live Plant Shade Perennial Magenta Red Flower Plumes---Gorgeous!!', 'astilbe-japonica-montgomery-live-plant-shade-perennial-magenta-red-flower-plumes-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0030', 'simple', 8, NULL, 'Shade Perennials', 26.20, NULL, 15.72, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/f9fc46/6214573809/il_fullxfull.6214573809_k9yo.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live plant that is 6\"- 8\" tall and growing! Want lots of color in your shade garden? Here ya go! In Spring, the fern-like foliage emerges bronze and then matures to green! In Summer, it explodes with magenta red dense flower plumes that make a great contrast against the leaves! You can leave the dried plumes in place during Winter for great visual interest!!\n\nCommon Name: \'Montgomery\' Astilbe \nBotanical Name: Astilbe japonica\nHardiness Zones: 4 - 8\nBloom Time: Summer\nSunlight: Part shade/full shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 1\' tall and 1\' to 2\' wide\nBloom Color: Magenta red\nEvergreen or Deciduous: Herbaceous perennial', '1 live plant that is 6\"- 8\" tall and growing! Want lots of color in your shade garden? Here ya go! In Spring, the fern-like foliage emerges bronze and then matures to green! In Summer, it explodes with magenta red dense...', '[\"Easy To Grow\",\"Shade Perennial\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Adds Texture\",\"Dramatic Foliage\",\"All Season Interest\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Container Plant\",\"Patio Garden\",\"Woodland Garden\",\"Wet Garden Area\",\"Deer Resistant\",\"Long Bloom Time\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:05', '2026-06-24 16:09:05'),
(303, 'Dwarf Japanese Maple \'Goshiki Kotohime\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Rare Tree Green Leaves Pink Cream Specks---Gorgeous!!', 'dwarf-japanese-maple-goshiki-kotohime-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-rare-tree-green-leaves-pink-cream-specks-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0031', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/96f566/7012402633/il_fullxfull.7012402633_47bi.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 plant that is 6\"- 8\" tall. This is a rare, highly sought-after dwarf Japanese maple that is an absolute favorite for small gardens, containers, and bonsai enthusiasts. The name Goshiki translates to \"five colors,\" hinting at the incredible changing canvas this tree provides throughout the seasons. What makes \'Goshiki kotohime\' truly unique is the way its leaves grow. The tiny, ruffled, five-lobed leaves grow incredibly tight and clustered along the upright branches. This dense, congested growth gives the stems a distinct, textured look—often described as looking like pipe cleaners or a bottle brush.\n\nSize (at 10 years): Roughly 3 to 6 feet tall and 2 to 3 feet wide. It maintains a very narrow, upright, V-shaped structure.  Growth Rate: Extremely slow, averaging only 4 to 8 inches of new growth per year.\n\nSpring: This is the tree\'s peak show. New growth emerges with a glowing soft orange or reddish tint, quickly shifting into a beautiful, impressionistic mix of bright pink, cream, white, and light green variegation.  \nSummer: The variegation gradually subdues as the leaves mature into a rich, handsome kelly green, though the tightly packed leaf arrangement keeps it looking highly textured. \nFall: The foliage transitions into a striking palette of bright gold, yellow-orange, and orange-red.\n\nSunlight: Morning sun with afternoon shade is the absolute sweet spot. Variegated leaves are highly susceptible to leaf scorch if exposed to intense, hot afternoon sun, especially in warmer climates.  Soil: It requires rich, consistently moist, but well-drained soil. Like all Japanese maples, they absolutely despise \"wet feet\" (standing water), which can cause root rot.  \nWatering: Water regularly to maintain even moisture. Do not let the soil dry out completely. Applying a layer of mulch around the base will help retain moisture and keep the root system cool.  Pruning: Minimal pruning is required due to its dwarf nature. If you do need to shape it or remove dead wood, only prune in the summer after the leaves have completely unfurled. Pruning in late winter or spring will cause the tree to \"bleed\" sap heavily.\n\nCommon Name: \'Goshiki Kotohime\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Full sun/part sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 3\' - 6\' tall and 2\' - 3\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 plant that is 6\"- 8\" tall.', '[\"Japanese Maples\",\"Dwarf Tree\",\"Variegated Leaves\",\"Bonsai Tree\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Rock Garden\",\"Small Garden Space\",\"Container Garden\",\"Small Leaves\",\"Slow Growth Rate\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Conifer Garden\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:05', '2026-06-24 16:09:05'),
(304, 'Japanese Maple \'Sister Ghost\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Rare Ghost Series Reticulated Yellow Green Leaves---Stunning!!', 'japanese-maple-sister-ghost-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-rare-ghost-series-reticulated-yellow-green-leaves-stunning', 'ETSY-0032', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/fdb2e1/6119135378/il_fullxfull.6119135378_9fsp.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 6\"- 8\" tall. A Ghost Series cultivar is one of the most stunning members of the famous \"Ghost Series\". It is highly prized for its dramatic reticulated variegation (prominent, dark veins contrasting against a lighter leaf body). While other cultivars in the Ghost series (like \'First Ghost\' or \'Grandmother Ghost\') push heavy pink or white tones, \'Sister Ghost\' focuses on an incredibly bright, luminous chartreuse-and-emerald contrast that instantly lightens up shady corners of a garden.\n\nSpring: Leaves emerge a striking, pale yellowish-green to creamy chartreuse with highly visible, dark green veins cutting through the center of each lobe.\n\nSummer: The contrast softens slightly as the leaf darkens to a more uniform light green, though the prominent vein structure remains a distinct texture.\n\nAutumn: The tree puts on a spectacular finale, shifting into vibrant shades of bright yellow, orange, and deep red.\n\nSize: It is a medium-sized, upright, and spreading tree, typically reaching 8–12 feet tall and about 6–8 feet wide over 10–15 years.\n\nSunlight: Like most pale or variegated maples, it thrives best in filtered sun or afternoon shade. Hot, direct afternoon sun can easily scorch its delicate, pale spring leaves.\n\nCommon Name: \'Sister Ghost\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum \nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Morning sun/Afternoon shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 8\' to 12\' tall and 6\' to 8\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 6\"- 8\" tall.', '[\"Rare Tree\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Leaf Contrast\",\"Dwarf Tree\",\"Reticulated Leaves\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Dramatic Fall Color\",\"Small Garden Space\",\"Container Tree\",\"Asian Garden\",\"Dark Veining\",\"Ghost Series\",\"Finely Toothed Leaf\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:05', '2026-06-24 16:09:05'),
(305, 'Japanese Maple \'Oregon Sunset\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Plum Colored Leaves---Gorgeous!!', 'japanese-maple-oregon-sunset-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-plum-colored-leaves-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0033', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/309066/5432910315/il_fullxfull.5432910315_8oi6.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 8\"- 10\" tall. This cultivar is a beautiful color and grows wider than it is tall! This tree is a highly prized semi-dwarf cultivar of the Japanese maple (Acer palmatum) known for its compact growth habit and brilliant, shifting color profile that mimics an actual sunset. Unlike upright red maples like \'Bloodgood\', \'Oregon Sunset\' offers a much more manageable dwarf stature combined with deeply divided, delicate palmate leaves that hold their vibrant hues incredibly well through the heat of summer.\n\nGrowth Habit & Size: It features a dense, round, and shrub-like form. It grows relatively slowly, typically reaching 8 to 10 feet tall and wide at maturity, making it an exceptional choice for small yards, containers, or accent plantings.\n\nSpring: Leaves emerge a bright, soft red to orange-red.\n\nSummer: The foliage transitions to a deep plum-burgundy or rich red-green, especially in softer light.\n\nAutumn: True to its name, the tree finishes the season with a spectacular, fiery explosion of bright orange, crimson, and golden-yellow tones.\n\nSunlight: Thrives best in partial shade to full sun. In hotter climates, afternoon shade is highly recommended to protect the delicate leaf margins from scorching.\n\nSoil: Requires moist, organically rich, well-draining soil. Like most Japanese maples, it prefers slightly acidic conditions and dislikes \"wet feet\" (poorly drained, soggy soil).\n\nCommon Name: \'Oregon Sunset\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Full sun/part sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 8\' to 10\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 8\"- 10\" tall.', '[\"Low Growing\",\"Spreading Shape\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Spring Color\",\"Fall Color\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Small Space\",\"Container Tree\",\"Asian Garden\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"City Garden\",\"Low Maintenance\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:05', '2026-06-24 16:09:05'),
(306, 'Mountain Laurel \'Olympic Fire\' Kalmia latifolia Live Plant Evergreen Shrub Dark Red Buds & Light Pink Flowers---Stunning!!', 'mountain-laurel-olympic-fire-kalmia-latifolia-live-plant-evergreen-shrub-dark-red-buds-light-pink-flowers-stunning', 'ETSY-0034', 'simple', 15, NULL, 'Evergreen Shrubs', 34.20, NULL, 20.52, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/c064ef/8047223154/il_fullxfull.8047223154_iw12.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live plant that is 6\" - 8\" tall ! Mountain Laurels are hard to find!! In late Spring/early Summer, it has dark red buds that open up into lighter pink flowers! It has a long bloom time, so you can enjoy gorgeous flowers for quite a while! It\'s compact size makes it a great choice for containers too!!\n\nCommon Name: \'Olympic Fire\' Mountain Laurel\nBotanical Name: Kalmia latifolia\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: Late Spring/early Summer \nSunlight: Part sun prefers morning sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 5\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: Light Pink\nEvergreen or Deciduous: Evergreen', '1 live plant that is 6\" - 8\" tall ! Mountain Laurels are hard to find!! In late Spring/early Summer, it has dark red buds that open up into lighter pink flowers! It has a long bloom time, so you can enjoy gorgeous flower...', '[\"Evergreen Shrub\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Long Bloom Time\",\"Small Garden Space\",\"Border Plant\",\"Container Garden\",\"Cut Flowers\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Attracts Butterflies\",\"Bee Friendly\",\"Compact Shape\",\"Low Informal Hedge\",\"Rabbit Resistant\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 12, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:0