(309, 'Japanese Maple \'Bort\'s Broom\' Acer Circinatum Live Grafted Dwarf Tree ---Stunning!!', 'japanese-maple-borts-broom-acer-circinatum-live-grafted-dwarf-tree-stunning', 'ETSY-0037', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/b36839/8210281367/il_fullxfull.8210281367_7izq.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 6\"- 8\" tall. This is a highly sought-after dwarf cultivar, but it is actually a variety of Acer circinatum (the Pacific Northwest native Vine Maple), rather than a true Acer palmatum (Japanese maple). Because it shares a similar delicate leaf structure, aesthetic, and care profile, specialty nurseries and collectors often group it right alongside Japanese maples. Because of its naturally compact, slow-growing, and well-behaved nature, it makes an excellent choice for rock gardens, small borders, or as a striking container specimen on a patio.\n\nGrowth & Size: It features an exceptionally dense, tight, multi-stemmed shrub form. Unlike the typically lanky, spreading habit of native vine maples, \'Bort\'s Broom\' is a true dwarf that generally maxes out around 3 to 4 feet tall and 2 feet wide over 10 years.  \n\nFoliage & Color Transformation: The leaves emerge a vibrant, fresh green in the spring. However, it reacts uniquely to sunlight: when exposed to sun, the outer edges and top leaves \"bronze out\" into a highly striking cherry red, giving the plant a beautiful two-toned contrast.  \n\nCommon Name: \'Bort\'s Broom\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer circinatum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Morning sun/Afternoon shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 3\' to 4\' tall and 2\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 6\"- 8\" tall.', '[\"Fall Color\",\"Japanese Maple\",\"Dramatic Color\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Specimen Tree\",\"Urban Garden\",\"Visual Interest\",\"Vibrant Leaf Color\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Color Contrast\",\"Dwarf\",\"Witches Broom\",\"Bonsai\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:06', '2026-06-24 16:09:06'),
(310, 'Japanese Maple \'Crispii\' Acer palmatum  Live Grafted Dwarf Tree Unique Leaves---Stunning!!', 'japanese-maple-crispii-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-dwarf-tree-unique-leaves-stunning', 'ETSY-0038', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/8b8b3c/8162307676/il_fullxfull.8162307676_7ctj.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live  grafted tree that is 8\"- 10\" tall. If you are looking for a true dwarf variety with a delicate, compact look, this is the one. It features deeply divided, emerald-green leaves in the summer that feature slightly crinkled or serrated texturing.\n\nSize: Very slow-growing, reaching only about 4 to 5 feet tall and wide over many years, giving it a beautiful mound or vase-like shape.  \n\nFall Color: Turns a brilliant, fiery orange and yellow before dropping its leaves.  \n\nBest For: Small urban gardens, containers, or accent spots where space is limited. \n\nLight: Partial shade is ideal. Afternoon shade protects their delicate or crinkled leaf margins from leaf scorch.  \n\nSoil: They prefer moist, organically rich, slightly acidic, and highly well-drained soil. They absolutely hate sitting in soggy, waterlogged dirt.\n\nCommon Name: \'Crispii\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Morning sun/Afternoon shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 4\' to 5\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 8\"- 10\" tall.', '[\"Fall Color\",\"Japanese Maple\",\"Dramatic Color\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Specimen Tree\",\"Urban Garden\",\"Visual Interest\",\"Vibrant Leaf Color\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Color Contrast\",\"Dwarf\",\"Container\",\"Bonsai\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 2, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:07', '2026-06-24 16:09:07'),
(311, 'Japanese Maple \'Purple Crunch\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Rare Dwarf Tree---Stunning!!', 'japanese-maple-purple-crunch-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-rare-dwarf-tree-stunning', 'ETSY-0039', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/4487ee/8162297258/il_fullxfull.8162297258_mvs8.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 10\"- 12\" tall. This cultivar is an extremely striking, rare dwarf Japanese maple cultivar known for its highly unique foliage texture and dramatic seasonal color shifts. It features 5-lobed palmate leaves with distinctive crinkled, heavily serrated, and slightly curled margins—giving it a heavily textured, \"crunchy\" visual appearance.\n\nSpring: Emerges a vibrant, rich purple-red.\n\nSummer: Matures to a deep dark blue-green, but regularly pushes out fresh flushes of bright purple new growth on contrasting red stems.\n\nFall: Transmutes into a glowing, fiery red.\n\nSize & Form: A slow-growing, upright dwarf variety. It typically reaches about 5 to 6 feet tall in 10 years, eventually maturing around 7 to 10 feet with a compact vase shape.\n\nLight Needs: Thrives best in morning sun with dappled or afternoon shade. Protection from the intense late-afternoon sun helps maintain the richest leaf colors without scorching the crinkled margins.\nSoil & Drainage: Requires moist, well-drained, slightly acidic soil. Perfect drainage is absolutely essential to prevent root issues.\nLandscape Use: Excellent for small gardens, borders, or long-term patio container culture (including bonsai).\n\nCommon Name: \'Purple crunch\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Full sun/part sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 5\' to 6\' tall and  wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 10\"- 12\" tall.', '[\"Fall Color\",\"Japanese Maple\",\"Dramatic Color\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Specimen Tree\",\"Urban Garden\",\"Visual Interest\",\"Vibrant Leaf Color\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Color Contrast\",\"Dwarf\",\"Bonsai\",\"Rare\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 2, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:07', '2026-06-24 16:09:07'),
