', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 3, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:07', '2026-06-24 16:09:07'),
(313, 'Astilbe japonica \'Peach Blossom\' Live Plant Shade Perennial Peachy Pink Flowers---Lovely!!', 'astilbe-japonica-peach-blossom-live-plant-shade-perennial-peachy-pink-flowers-lovely', 'ETSY-0041', 'simple', 8, NULL, 'Shade Perennials', 26.20, NULL, 15.72, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/e56ad0/6679192362/il_fullxfull.6679192362_5nn3.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live plant that is 6\"- 8\" tall.  This absolutely gorgeous compact shade perennial definitely stands out!! In early Summer, it explodes with plumes of peachy pink flowers on long stems that make a great contrast against the fern-like shiny green leaves!! The flowers are long lasting for even more to love about this plant! The long stems make it an excellent choice for cut flower arrangements too!!\n\n\nCommon Name: \'Peach Blossom\' Astilbe\nBotanical Name: Astilbe japonica\nHardiness Zones: 4 - 9\nBloom Time: Early Summer\nSunlight: Part shade/shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 1\' to 2\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: Peach\nEvergreen or Deciduous: Herbaceous perennial', '1 live plant that is 6\"- 8\" tall.', '[\"Shade Perennial\",\"Cut Flowers\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Woodland Garden\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Unique Flowers\",\"Container Garden\",\"Border Plant\",\"Pond Border\",\"Plant In Groups\",\"Long Bloom Time\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Attracts Pollinators\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 8, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:07', '2026-06-24 16:09:07'),
(314, 'Japanese Maple \'Tsuchigumo\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Unique Leaves---Stunning!!', 'japanese-maple-tsuchigumo-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-unique-leaves-stunning', 'ETSY-0042', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/65421b/8124223391/il_fullxfull.8124223391_a8rt.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 8\"- 10\" tall. Its name meaning \"ground spider\' reflects the downward crinkle of its leaves. In Spring, its leaves emerge in red hue and transition to a vibrant green all summer! The show continues in Fall when the leaves change to bright gold with crimson edges! This upright semi-dwarf has a vase shaped growth habit making it great to plant as a specimen in your landscape!!\n\nCommon Name: \'Tsuchigumo\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Full sun/part sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 6\' to 8\' tall and 4\' to 5\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 8\"- 10\" tall.', '[\"Fall Color\",\"Japanese Maple\",\"Dramatic Color\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Specimen Tree\",\"Urban Garden\",\"Visual Interest\",\"Vibrant Leaf Color\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Color Contrast\",\"Unique Bark\",\"Semi-Dwarf\",\"Downward Leaves\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 2, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:07', '2026-06-24 16:09:07'),
(315, 'Mountain Laurel \'Tiddlywinks\' Starter Plant Flowering Shrub Pink Buds Light Pink Flowers---Gorgeous!!', 'mountain-laurel-tiddlywinks-starter-plant-flowering-shrub-pink-buds-light-pink-flowers-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0043', 'simple', 7, NULL, 'Flowering Shrubs', 25.20, NULL, 15.12, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/2eae3e/6286700600/il_fullxfull.6286700600_kaus.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live starter plant that is 2\" - 4\" tall! Mountain Laurels are hard to find!! In late Spring/early Summer, it has bright pink buds that open up into soft pink flowers! The stamens are very visible and make a unique star shaped pattern inside the flower! It has a long bloom time, so you can enjoy gorgeous flowers for quite a while! It\'s compact size makes it a great choice for containers too!!\n\nCommon Name: \'Tiddlywinks\' Mountain Laurel\nBotanical Name: Kalmia latifolia\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: Late Spring/early Summer \nSunlight: Part sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 3\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: Pink\nEvergreen or Deciduous: Evergreen', '1 live starter plant that is 2\" - 4\" tall! Mountain Laurels are hard to find!! In late Spring/early Summer, it has bright pink buds that open up into soft pink flowers! The stamens are very visible and make a unique star...', '[\"Easy To Grow\",\"Long Bloom Time\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Bee Friendly\",\"Attracts Pollinators\",\"Hard To Find Shrub\",\"Evergreen Shrub\",\"Container Plant\",\"Small Garden Space\",\"Abundant Flowers\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Woodland Garden\",\"Compact And Bushy\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL,