(317, 'Hydrangea Serrata \'Bluebird\' Live Plant Blue Or Pink Lacecap Flowers---Gorgeous!!', 'hydrangea-serrata-bluebird-live-plant-blue-or-pink-lacecap-flowers-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0045', 'simple', 10, NULL, 'Hydrangeas', 24.75, NULL, 14.85, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/31daab/3968236711/il_fullxfull.3968236711_cktz.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for live plants that are 6\"- 8\" tall and multi-branched. An absolutely beautiful variety is a classic, highly celebrated lacecap variety of mountain hydrangea. Known for its elegant, delicate look and exceptional cold hardiness, it\'s a favorite for adding soft texture and striking color to shady garden spots.\n\nAs a lacecap hydrangea, its bloom heads feature a flattened center of tiny, fuzzy-looking fertile florets, ringed by an outer circle of large, showy, star-like sterile sepals.\n\nColor-Shifting Nature: Like many hydrangeas, its color depends entirely on soil pH. In acidic soil with high aluminum availability, it produces a striking, vivid sky blue to deep purple-blue. In alkaline or neutral soils, the flowers shift to a lovely pale pink or mauve.\n\nFoliage: The dark green leaves have lightly serrated edges, turning a gorgeous coppery-red or deep burgundy in the autumn.\n\nSize: It grows into a compact, rounded mounded shrub, typically reaching 3 to 5 feet tall and wide at maturity.\n\nCommon Name: \'Bluebird\' Hydrangea\nBotanical Name: Hydrangea serrata\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: Late Spring\nSunlight: Part sun/part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 3\' to 5\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: Blue or purplish pink depending on soil acidity\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', 'live plants that are 6\"- 8\" tall and multi-branched.', '[\"Lacecap Flowers\",\"Easy Care\",\"Cut Flowers\",\"Foundation Planting\",\"Specimen Plant\",\"Accent Plant\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Urban Garden\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Border Plant\",\"Container Plant\",\"Low Hedge\",\"Pollinator Plant\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 3, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:08', '2026-06-24 16:09:08'),
(318, 'Japanese Maple \'Cotton Candy\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Rare Pink White Green Variegated Leaves---Stunning!!', 'japanese-maple-cotton-candy-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-rare-pink-white-green-variegated-leaves-stunning', 'ETSY-0046', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/f57aab/6167395789/il_fullxfull.6167395789_hdwz.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 10\"- 12\" tall. This variegated cultivar is a striking, highly sought-after variegated Japanese maple. It is best known for its pastel color palette and dynamic seasonal transformations. Because \'Cotton Candy\' features heavy white and pink variegation (which lacks chlorophyll), the leaves are more fragile than standard green or purple maples.\n\nSpring: The tree earns its name in the spring. New growth pushes out with intense, fluffy shades of bright pink, cream, and soft white over a light green base. The variegation pattern can be quite heavy, sometimes completely taking over new leaf flushes.\n\nSummer: As the season progresses and heat increases, the pink tones gradually tone down to a muted pastel pink or fade entirely, leaving a crisp cream-and-green variegated leaf pattern.\n\nAutumn: In the fall, the foliage shifts to brilliant shades of orange and deep red.\n\nSize: It is considered a semi-dwarf to medium-sized tree. It typically reaches 6 to 8 feet tall and about 4 to 5 feet wide over a span of 10 years, making it an excellent choice for smaller gardens, containers, or focal landscape beds.\n\nStructure: It grows with an upright, densely branching habit that naturally forms a compact, rounded canopy.\n\nSunlight: Morning sun and afternoon shade is highly recommended. Intense afternoon sun will easily scorch the delicate white and pink margins, turning them crispy and brown.\n\nSoil: Like most Japanese maples, it thrives in well-drained, slightly acidic soil. It does not tolerate heavy, soggy clay or \"wet feet.\"\n\nCommon Name: \'Cotton Candy\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum \nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Morning sun/Afternoon shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 6\' to 8\' tall and 4\' to 5\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 10\"- 12\" tall.', '[\"Rare Tree\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Woodland Garden\",\"Unusual Leaf Color\",\"Summer Interest\",\"Brilliant Fall Color\",\"Variegated Leaves\",\"Small Garden Space\",\"New Cultivar\",\"Pink Stems\",\"Low Maintenance\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 2, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:08', '2026-06-24 16:09:08'),
(319, 'Japanese Maple \'Amagi Shigure\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Dwarf Brick Red Leaves Dark Veining---Stunning!!', 'japanese-maple-amagi-shigure-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-dwarf-brick-red-leaves-dark-veining-stunning', 'ETSY-0047', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/3976de/6074867170/il_fullxfull.6074867170_h48j.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 6\"- 8\" tall. This dwarf cultivar definitely has a wow factor and is widely considered one of the most breathtaking reticulated (veined) Japanese maples available. If you love high-contrast foliage and dramatic seasonal color shifts, this cultivar is a showstopper.\n\nSpring Foliage: Its absolute peak season. In early spring, the leaves emerge a shocking, electric bright pink to magenta with dark purple-black veins sharply tracing every lobe.\n\nSummer Transition: As the heat sets in, the pink tones gradually soften into a brick-red or deep purple-bronze, while the dark veining remains highly prominent.\n\nFall Finale: The tree finishes the growing season with a spectacular burst of blazing orange-red to bright crimson.\n\nSize: It is a slow-to-moderate grower with a dense, upright, and multi-branched form. It typically reaches about 6 to 8 feet tall and 4 to 5 feet wide over 10 years, making it an excellent choice for smaller gardens or large containers.\n\nSun Exposure: To prevent the intense pink pigment from bleaching or scorching, it thrives best in dappled shade or morning sun with afternoon protection. Too much deep shade will cause the bright colors to fade to a duller green-purple.\n\nSoil: Like most Japanese maples, it demands moist, organically rich, well-draining soil. It absolutely hates sitting in stagnant water or soggy clay.\n\nCommon Name: \'Amagi Shigure\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum \nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Morning sun/Afternoon shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 6\' to 8\' tall and 4\' to 5\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 6\"- 8\" tall.', '[\"Easy To Grow\",\"Dwarf Tree\",\"Reticulated Leaves\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Brilliant Fall Color\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Small Garden Space\",\"Container Garden\",\"Woodland Garden\",\"Ornamental Tree\",\"Focal Point\",\"Bonsai Tree\",\"Low Maintenance\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:08', '2026-06-24 16:09:08'),
(320, 'Japanese Maple \'Koto Maru\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Dwarf Tree Yellow Leaves With Red Edges---Beautiful!!', 'japanese-maple-koto-maru-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-dwarf-tree-yellow-leaves-with-red-edges-beautiful', 'ETSY-0048', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/9582f8/5825542240/il_fullxfull.5825542240_qj0d.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 8\"- 10\" tall. This beautiful variety has a lot to offer! This cultivar is a highly unique, ultra-dwarf Japanese maple. Discovered as a witches\' broom mutation, it features incredibly tight, compact growth and tiny foliage, making it a favorite for small gardens, containers, and bonsai enthusiasts.\n\nSpring: Leaves emerge small and densely packed, showcasing a lime-green or yellow-green center often highlighted by a distinct bronze or pinkish-red margin on the outer edges.  \n\nSummer: The foliage matures into a deeper, crisp green. A neat visual trait of \'Koto maru\' is that its middle leaf lobe is notably shortened, giving the tiny leaves a distinct multi-pointed look that some growers describe as resembling little birds with open wings. \n\nAutumn: It finishes the season with an intense display of brilliant crimson reds, oranges, and golden yellows. \n\nSize: Extremely slow-growing. It typically reaches only 3 to 4 feet tall and wide over 10 years, eventually topping out around 5 to 6 feet at full maturity. It forms a dense, bushy, rounded shrub naturally.  \nExposure: Thrives in full sun to partial shade. In hotter southern climates, dappled afternoon shade is highly recommended to protect the delicate, tiny leaves from scorching.  \nSoil: Requires rich, evenly moist, but strictly well-drained soil. Like most Japanese maples, it does not tolerate soggy roots (\"wet feet\").\n\nCommon Name: \'Koto Maru\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Full sun/part sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 3\' to 4\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 8\"- 10\" tall.', '[\"Japanese Maple\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Dwarf Tree\",\"Container Plant\",\"Patio Garden\",\"Fall Color\",\"Small Leaves\",\"Courtyard Garden\",\"Dainty Tree\",\"Small Garden\",\"Drought Tolerant\",\"Unique Texture\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 3, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:09', '2026-06-24 16:09:09'),
(321, 'Japanese Maple \'Hana Matoi\' Acer palmatum dissectum Live Grafted Tree Weeping Pink Laceleaf---Gorgeous!!', 'japanese-maple-hana-matoi-acer-palmatum-dissectum-live-grafted-tree-weeping-pink-laceleaf-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0049', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/fa0caa/5324080868/il_fullxfull.5324080868_a90h.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 8\"- 10\" tall. This weeping cultivar is one of the most striking and colorful variegated laceleaf Japanese maples available today.  Its name beautifully translates from Japanese as \"adorned with flowers\"—a perfect description for a dwarf tree whose multi-toned foliage mimics the look of a blooming shrub throughout the season. \'Hana matoi\' originated as a natural sport (a genetic mutation) from another famous variegated cultivar, \'Toyama nishiki\'. However, \'Hana matoi\' holds its variegation much more reliably without reverting back to plain green, and its pink tones are noticeably brighter and more intense.  It has a slow-growing, pendulous (weeping) habit that naturally forms a cascading, umbrella-like mound. Over 10 years, it typically reaches just 3 to 5 feet tall and spreads about 4 to 6 feet wide, making it an elite choice for small gardens, rock gardens, focal points, or container planting.  \n\nSpring: Leaves emerge a deep burgundy-purple or maroon, heavily streaked and splashed with brilliant hot pink and cream.  \nSummer: The base color transitions to a rich green, but it retains its vibrant pink and white variegation. The contrast looks incredibly striking in shifting light.  \nAutumn: The tree puts on a dramatic finale, changing to shades of fiery orange and vibrant cherry red.  Winter: As an added bonus, the bark displays a distinct yellow hue that becomes brighter and more pronounced during the cold winter months.  \n\nLight Exposure: Morning sun with afternoon shade is highly recommended. The delicate pink and white variegated sections are prone to leaf scorch under harsh, direct afternoon heat.\nWatering: Prefers consistent, even moisture. It does not tolerate drought well when young, but equally dislikes \"wet feet\" (waterlogged soil).\nSoil Needs: Rich, organic, and well-draining soil with a slightly acidic pH (5.5–6.5).\n\nCommon Name: \'Hana Matoi\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum dissectum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Part sun/part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 3\' - 5\' tall and 4\' to 6\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 8\"- 10\" tall.', '[\"Unique Leaves\",\"Laceleaf Tree\",\"Small Spaces\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Fall Color\",\"Zen Garden\",\"Specimen Tree\",\"Umbrella Shape\",\"Sun Tolerant\",\"Deer Resistant\",\"Container Tree\",\"Disease Resistant\",\"Dwarf Tree\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:09', '2026-06-24 16:09:09'),
(322, 'Dwarf Japanese Maple \'Dell\'s Dwarf\' Acer circinatum Grafted Live Tree – Bonsai Candidate', 'dwarf-japanese-maple-dells-dwarf-acer-circinatum-grafted-live-tree-bonsai-candidate', 'ETSY-0050', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/d63981/8207182743/il_fullxfull.8207182743_trpa.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 plant that is 6\" - 8\" tall. This rare grafted variety has a lot to offer! This tree is a standout dwarf cultivar highly prized for its unique growth habit, vibrant seasonal color transitions, and exceptional suitability for bonsai. While it is often grouped with or marketed alongside Japanese maples due to its striking look and compact growth, \'Del\'s Dwarf\' (sometimes spelled Dell\'s Dwarf) is actually a choice dwarf cultivar of the Vine Maple (Acer circinatum), a species native to the Pacific Northwest.  Because vine maples are close genetic cousins to Asian maples, they share a very similar landscape aesthetic. If you are looking for an eye-catching, multi-season color show in a small footprint, this is an exceptional pick. \n\nFoliage & \"Autumn in Summer\" Effect: The small, deeply lobed leaves emerge in spring with striking Mediterranean tones of rosy-copper, peach, and orange-green. In summer, the foliage transitions into a complex mix of light green, yellow, and apricot—giving it an autumn-like look all season long.  \n\nFall Color: In October, it finishes the year with an explosive display of brilliant yellows, burning oranges, and intense reds.  \n\nGrowth Habit & Size: This is a true dwarf. It grows very slowly into a tight, densely branched, rounded \"poof\" or multi-stemmed shrub. It typically reaches only 3 to 5 feet tall and wide after 10 years, making it an excellent candidate for small garden borders, rock gardens, or container planting.  \n\nSun Exposure: Full sun to partial shade (shows its best multi-toned colors with some dappled shade)\nWater Needs: Prefers consistent moisture; more sun-tolerant than other colorful vine maples if kept watered\nSoil Type: Rich, well-draining, acidic to neutral soil; tolerates clay better than many Acer palmatum varieties\n\nCommon Name: \'Dell\'s Dwarf\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer circinatum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Morning Sun/Afternoon Shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 3\' - 5\' tall and wide \nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 plant that is 6\" - 8\" tall.', '[\"Japanese Maples\",\"Dwarf Tree\",\"Rare Tree\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Small Garden Space\",\"Rock Garden\",\"Fairy Garden\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Brilliant Fall Color\",\"Vibrant Color\",\"Bonsai Tree\",\"Small Leaves\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:09', '2026-06-24 16:09:09'),
(323, 'Japanese Maple \'Tenuifolium\' Acer shirasawanum Live Grafted Tree Rare Full Moon Green Serrated Leaves---Hard To Find!!', 'japanese-maple-tenuifolium-acer-shirasawanum-live-grafted-tree-rare-full-moon-green-serrated-leaves-hard-to-find', 'ETSY-0051', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/56b8d5/6061987113/il_fullxfull.6061987113_mut0.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 10\" - 12\" tall. You don\'t see this Full Moon variety very often...it\'s rare and hard to find! It has green Full Moon-like leaves that are more serrated than other shirasawanum! \n\nFoliage: The leaves are relatively small (about 2 to 3 inches across) and feature 9 to 11 narrow, finely textured lobes. In the spring, the papery-thin foliage emerges as a brilliant, translucent light green or lime green, often margined with soft, silky hairs. The delicate texture gives the tree a beautiful, airy, fan-like canopy.  \n\nFall Color: True to its Full Moon lineage, its autumn display is exceptional. The canopy transforms into an intense palette of bright golden-yellows, rich oranges, and fiery crimson reds.\n\nGrowth Habit & Size: It features an open, layered, and upright form with slender grey-to-red branches. While it grows moderately well in its youth, its growth eventually slows down. In a garden setting, it typically matures into a small, elegant tree around 10 feet tall, though under ideal woodland conditions over many decades, it can reach larger proportions. Its seeds are notably held upright above the delicate foliage.\n\nSun & Shade: Because its leaves are exceptionally thin and delicate, Tenuifolium is highly susceptible to leaf scorch. It performs best in partial or dappled shade and must be protected from hot afternoon sun.  \nSoil & Moisture: Prefers consistently moist, well-draining, and slightly acidic soil. It does not tolerate drought well, so mulching around the root zone is highly recommended to retain moisture and keep the roots cool.\nBest Uses: Due to its slower growth habit and stunning, intricate leaf structure, it makes an absolute standout specimen for small courtyard gardens, Japanese-style woodland borders, container planting, and it is highly prized for bonsai training.\n\nCommon Name: \'Tenuifolium\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer shirasawanum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Morning Sun/Afternoon shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 8\' to 10\' tall \nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 10\" - 12\" tall.', '[\"Rare Tree\",\"Hard To Find\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Brilliant Fall Color\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Uncommon Tree\",\"Full Moon Maple\",\"Upright Growth\",\"Specimen Tree\",\"Visual Texture\",\"Mid-Sized Tree\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:09', '2026-06-24 16:09:09'),
(324, 'Hydrangea macrophylla \"Penny Mac\" Live Plant Perennial Mophead Flowers---Gorgeous!!', 'hydrangea-macrophylla-penny-mac-live-plant-perennial-mophead-flowers-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0052', 'simple', 10, NULL, 'Hydrangeas', 24.75, NULL, 14.85, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/89fcf4/8152755220/il_fullxfull.8152755220_klmj.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live plant that is 6\"-8\" tall and multi-branched. This beautiful variety is a highly popular, resilient bigleaf mophead variety. It stands out as an exceptional choice for home landscapes due to its unique blooming habits and reliable cold hardiness.\n\nReblooming Power (Remontant): Unlike traditional bigleaf hydrangeas that only bloom once on \"old wood\" (the previous year\'s stems), \'Penny Mac\' blooms on both old and new wood. This means even if a harsh winter kills the branches down to the ground, the new shoots that emerge in the spring will still produce beautiful flower clusters late in the summer.\n\nSoil Type	              Soil pH	              Bloom Color	                                  How to Achieve It\nHighly Acidic	Less than 5.5	Vibrant Blue / Purple	Add aluminum sulfate to the soil in spring.\nAlkaline	             Greater than 6.5	Clear Pink / Rose               Add garden lime to the soil in spring\n\nCommon Name: \"Penny Mac\" Hydrangea\nBotanical Name: Hydrangea macrophylla\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: Summer\nSunlight: Part sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 4\' - 6\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: Depends on soil PH\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live plant that is 6\"-8\" tall and multi-branched.', '[\"Pollinator\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Summer Flowers\",\"Unique\",\"Compact\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Urban Garden\",\"Specimen\",\"Foundation Shrub\",\"Container\",\"Cut Flowers\",\"Woodland Garden\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 10, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:10', '2026-06-24 16:09:10'),
(325, 'Japanese Maple \'Cosmos\' Acer Palmatum Grafted Tree: Upright Multi-Colored Leaves', 'japanese-maple-cosmos-acer-palmatum-grafted-tree-upright-multi-colored-leaves', 'ETSY-0053', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/e8f32b/8207151671/il_fullxfull.8207151671_sy73.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 8\"- 12\" tall. This variety grows in a narrow and upright form! This cultivar s a highly sought-after, heavily variegated Japanese maple known for its stunning multi-colored foliage and upright growth habit.\n\nFoliage & Color: New growth emerges as a bright coral pink in spring. During summer, the leaves develop a consistent, heavy pink, white, and green variegation that holds exceptionally well through the heat. In autumn, the foliage transforms into brilliant shades of orange and yellow.  \n\nSize & Shape: It features an open, bushy branching structure. Over a 10-year period, it typically reaches a mature height of 7 to 10 feet and a width of 4 to 6 feet, making it excellent for smaller yards, patios, or container planting. \n\nCare & Conditions: This cultivar thrives in well-drained soil and does best with morning sun and afternoon shade to protect its delicate variegated leaves from scorching.\n\n\n\nCommon Name: \'Cosmos\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Morning sun/Afternoon shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 7\' to 10\' tall and 4\' to 6\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 8\"- 12\" tall.', '[\"Japanese Maples\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Narrow Tree\",\"Upright Growth\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Brilliant Fall Color\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Narrow Form\",\"Attractive Bark\",\"Visual Interest\",\"Deer Resistant\",\"Small Garden Space\",\"Rare\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 2, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:10', '2026-06-24 16:09:10'),
(326, 'Japanese Maple \'Baby Ghost\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Ghost Series Rare Red Purple Leaves---Hard To Find!!', 'japanese-maple-baby-ghost-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-ghost-series-rare-red-purple-leaves-hard-to-find', 'ETSY-0054', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/3af397/6107803320/il_fullxfull.6107803320_2xdg.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 8\"- 10\" tall. A Ghost Series cultivar that is an incredible, dwarf addition to the famous \"Ghost Series\" of Japanese maples. If you love dramatic, shifting seasonal colors but have limited space, this one is an absolute standout. Like its larger relatives (such as \'Amber Ghost\' or \'Sister Ghost\'), \'Baby Ghost\' features striking reticulated variegation. This means the leaf veins display a sharply contrasting color against the main leaf tissue.\n\nSpring: Leaves emerge with bright tones of fiery red, orange, and pink, with darker, prominent veining showing through.\n\nSummer: The foliage transitions to soft greens and bronze shades, though the distinct vein patterns remain visible.\n\nAutumn: It puts on a spectacular finale with vibrant, blazing orange to deep red tones.\n\nSize & Habit: This is a true dwarf variety. It typically reaches only about 4 to 5 feet tall and wide over 10 years, growing into a dense, beautifully rounded, bushy shrub. Its compact nature makes it absolutely perfect for container gardening, patios, or small courtyard gardens.\n\nLight: It thrives best in partial shade. Morning sun followed by afternoon shade is ideal. Too much hot, direct afternoon sun can scorch the delicate, variegated leaves, while full shade may cause the distinct reticulated patterns to fade into a solid green.\n\nSoil: Plant it in well-draining, slightly acidic soil. Japanese maples hate having \"wet feet,\" so ensure excellent drainage whether it is in the ground or a pot.\n\nCommon Name: \'Baby Ghost\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum \nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Morning sun/Afternoon shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 4\' to 5\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 8\"- 10\" tall.', '[\"Rare Tree\",\"Small Tree\",\"Small Garden Space\",\"Patio Garden\",\"Bonsai Tree\",\"Reticulated Leaves\",\"Unique Leaf Color\",\"Brilliant Fall Color\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Dwarf Tree\",\"Courtyard Garden\",\"Ornamental Tree\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 2, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:10', '2026-06-24 16:09:10'),
(327, 'Japanese Maple \'Kurenai Jishi\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Dwarf Red Lion Twisted Leaves---Beautiful!!', 'japanese-maple-kurenai-jishi-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-dwarf-red-lion-twisted-leaves-beautiful', 'ETSY-0055', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/6de41c/6180788484/il_fullxfull.6180788484_tldq.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 6\"- 8\" tall. This is a gorgeous Red Lion dwarf cultivar and is a spectacular, highly structural dwarf cultivar. It is a witch\'s broom mutation found on the popular green \'Shishigashira\' (Lion\'s Head) maple, meaning it inherits that signature tightly crinkled, bunched-up foliage but adds intense red coloration. Because of its compact, slow growth and exceptionally dense, gnarled branching pattern, \'Kurenai jishi\' is also a highly prized choice for bonsai enthusiasts.\n\nFoliage Texture: The leaves are small, deeply divided, and uniquely crinkled or curled, growing in dense, compact tufts along short, stiff branches. This gives the tree an incredibly architectural, texture-heavy look.\n\nSpring: Emerges a bright, vibrant crimson or ruby red.\n\nSummer: Matures to a deep burgundy-purple. In hot climates, it may soften to a bronzy-green or dark maroon.\n\nAutumn: Puts on a dramatic show of brilliant orange to fiery red.\n\nSize & Growth Habit: It is a slow-growing dwarf with a naturally upright, multi-stemmed, and bushy form. Expect it to reach only about 4 to 5 feet tall and 3 feet wide over a 10-year period, making it perfect for smaller gardens, rockeries, or large containers.\n\nLight: Throws its best color in full sun to partial shade. In scorching hot climates, afternoon filtered shade is highly recommended to prevent the tightly packed leaf tips from burning.\n\nSoil: Requires moist, well-draining, acidic soil. Like most Japanese maples, it hates sitting in soggy, waterlogged ground.\n\nCommon Name: \'Kurenai Jishi\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum \nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Morning sun/Afternoon shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 4\' to 5\' tall and 3\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 6\"- 8\" tall.', '[\"Dwarf Tree\",\"Red Lion\",\"Small Garden Space\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Rock Garden\",\"Container Tree\",\"Bonsai Tree\",\"Woodland Garden\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Brilliant Fall Color\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Adds Texture\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 3, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:10', '2026-06-24 16:09:10'),
(328, 'Gardenia jasminoides \"Frostproof\" Live Plant Evergreen Perennial Shrub Showy White Fragrant Flowers---Beautiful!!', 'gardenia-jasminoides-frostproof-live-plant-evergreen-perennial-shrub-showy-white-fragrant-flowers-beautiful', 'ETSY-0056', 'simple', 3, NULL, 'Perennials', 23.75, NULL, 14.25, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/ae7133/8200076649/il_fullxfull.8200076649_jvyf.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\n     This listing is for a live plant that is 6\" to 8\" tall and multi-branched. This is a beautiful evergreen variety that has dark green glossy leaves and puts on a show in Summer! It produces an abundance of double ivory-white flowers that are highly fragrant and measure 2\"-3\" across! You will want to plant these close to your patio or porch so you can enjoy the sweet fragrance! It grows in a rounded shape and is perfect to use as a specimen or plant a bunch for a gorgeous low hedge! It also reblooms in Fall...wow!!\n\nCommon Name: \"Frostproof\" Gardenia\nBotanical Name: Gardenia jasminoides\nHardiness Zones: 7 - 11\nSunlight: Morning Sun/Afternoon Shade\nSoil Requirements: Not picky about the soil\nMature Size: 3\' to 4\' tall and wide\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Evergreen (Zones 8-11)', 'a live plant that is 6\" to 8\" tall and multi-branched.', '[\"Pollinator\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Summer Flowers\",\"Fragrant\",\"Showy\",\"Cut Flowers\",\"Specimen\",\"Container\",\"Mass Planting\",\"Rebloomer\",\"Evergreen\",\"Deer Resistant\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 14, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:10', '2026-06-24 16:09:10'),
(329, 'Red Formosa Azalea Live Plant – Magenta Fuchsia Blooms, Semi-Evergreen Shrub', 'red-formosa-azalea-live-plant-magenta-fuchsia-blooms-semi-evergreen-shrub', 'ETSY-0057', 'simple', 15, NULL, 'Evergreen Shrubs', 23.30, NULL, 13.98, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/814165/7881943370/il_fullxfull.7881943370_fc7o.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live plant that is 8\"- 10\" tall and multi-branched. This beautiful plant has so much to offer! It is an semi-evergreen (evergreen zone 8 to 10) southern ornamental shrub has medium to dark green leaves. In Spring, it explodes with gorgeous flowers that are magenta/fuchsia to red that really stands out! It has an upright growth habit with a rounded shape and makes a great hedge! \n\nCommon Name: \"Red Formosa\" Azalea\nBotanical Name: Azalea indica\nHardiness Zones: 7 - 10\nBloom Time: Spring, Summer\nSunlight: Morning sun and afternoon shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 6\' to 8\' tall and 4\' to 6\' wide\nBloom Color: Magenta/Fuchsia to Red\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Semi-Evergreen', '1 live plant that is 8\"- 10\" tall and multi-branched.', '[\"Low Maintenance\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Compact\",\"Hedge\",\"Specimen\",\"Rebloomer\",\"Heat Resistant\",\"Drought Resistant\",\"Disease Resistant\",\"Fast Growing\",\"Vibrant Color\",\"Spring Flowers\",\"Fuchsia Color\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 13, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:11', '2026-06-24 16:09:11'),
(330, 'Japanese Maple \'Olsen\'s Frosted Strawberry\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Variegated Reticulated Leaves---Stunning!!', 'japanese-maple-olsens-frosted-strawberry-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-variegated-reticulated-leaves-stunning', 'ETSY-0058', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/e5caec/7012396367/il_fullxfull.7012396367_84ti.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 plant that is 8\"- 10\" tall. This variegated grafted variety has a lot to offer! This is a highly sought-after, collector-grade dwarf Japanese maple. It is famous for its heavily reticulated leaves (meaning they have prominent, contrasting veins) and shifting neon colors.\n\nThis tree acts like living art, shifting dramatically depending on the month:\nSpring: Leaves emerge a luminous, intense strawberry-pink to bright pinkish-red, heavily accented with deep burgundy or purple veins.\nSummer: The \"frosted\" look takes over. The older leaves soften to a creamy white or pale mint-green background with distinct red-to-green veins. Meanwhile, hot weather triggers a second flush of new growth that pops as bright pinkish-red over the frosted older canopy.  \nFall: The foliage turns to a fiery finale of bright yellow-orange, rust, and glowing scarlet red before dropping for winter.\n\n\"Avoid heavy fertilizing. Variegated and reticulated Japanese maples like \'Olsen\'s Frosted Strawberry\' can actually lose their beautiful variegation and revert to plain green if they are given too much nitrogen fertilizer. If planted in the ground, they rarely need any supplemental feeding at all.\"\n\nSun Exposure: Morning Sun / Afternoon Shade (Crucial). The delicate, variegated leaves need morning light to bring out the pinks, but intense afternoon sun will easily scorch and crisp the foliage.\nSoil Type: Rich, organic, slightly acidic soil.\nDrainage: Excellent drainage is mandatory. Like most Japanese maples, it absolutely hates \"wet feet\" (soggy, saturated soil), which easily leads to root rot.\nWatering: Keep the soil consistently moist but not waterlogged. Container-grown trees will need much more frequent watering as pots dry out quickly.\n\nCommon Name: \'Olsen\'s Frosted Strawberry\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Full sun/part sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 5\'-6\' tall and 4\'-6\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 plant that is 8\"- 10\" tall.', '[\"Japanese Maples\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Small Garden Space\",\"Reticulated Leaves\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Variegated Leaves\",\"Vibrant Color\",\"Unique Leaf Color\",\"Brilliant Fall Color\",\"Ornamental Tree\",\"Accent Tree\",\"Woodland Garden\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:11', '2026-06-24 16:09:11'),
(331, 'Japanese Maple \'Lileeanne\'s Jewel\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Variegated Pink White Red Leaves---Hard To Find!!', 'japanese-maple-lileeannes-jewel-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-variegated-pink-white-red-leaves-hard-to-find', 'ETSY-0059', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/448417/5390981762/il_fullxfull.5390981762_7bt3.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 10\" - 12\" tall. This is another rare fabulous grafted variegated variety with non-stop color! If you are looking for a show-stopping focal point, this tree delivers a striking display of colors across the seasons. \n\nThe Foliage: The leaves are heavily divided, narrow, and often slightly sickle-shaped or curled.\nHigh Stability: Many variegated red Japanese maples are notorious for \"reverting\" back to solid green or solid red. \'Lileeanne\'s Jewel\' is highly celebrated because its multi-colored patterns remain exceptionally stable year after year.\nSpring: Leaves emerge a vibrant burgundy-red heavily splashed and mottled with hot pink.\nSummer: The base color shifts to a deeper burgundy-green, while the variegation cools into a beautiful matrix of pink, cream-white, and green.\nFall: A final explosion of bright crimson reds deeply infused with electric pink variegation.\n\nSize & Growth Habit: It develops a small, upright, slightly bushy or mounded shape. It grows at a slow-to-moderate rate, typically reaching 8 to 10 feet tall and 5 to 6 feet wide over 10 to 15 years. This compact size makes it excellent for smaller garden beds or large patio containers.\nSun Exposure: It does best in morning sun with afternoon shade (or all-day dappled light). While it is noted for being fairly heat-tolerant with minimal leaf scorch compared to older variegated varieties, the pink and white margins can still burn if subjected to punishing afternoon sun in hotter climates.\n\nGolden Rule for Care: Do not over-fertilize. Heavy chemical fertilizers can push out rapid growth that temporary dilutes or overrides the variegation. Stick to organic-rich, well-draining soil and a light layer of mulch to keep the roots cool. If any rare solid-red or solid-green branches appear, simply prune them out to preserve the tree\'s patterned look.\n\nCommon Name: \'Lileeanne\'s Jewel\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum \nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Full sun/part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 8\' to 10\' tall and 5\' to 6\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 10\" - 12\" tall.', '[\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Spring Color\",\"Fall Color\",\"Unique Leaf Color\",\"Variegated Leaves\",\"Multi-Season Color\",\"Asian Garden\",\"Rock Garden\",\"Small Tree\",\"Container Plant\",\"Dwarf Tree\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"City Garden\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 4, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:11', '2026-06-24 16:09:11'),
(332, 'Japanese Maple \'Uncle Ghost\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Ghost Series Reticulated Peach Pink Cream Leaves---Stunning!!', 'japanese-maple-uncle-ghost-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-ghost-series-reticulated-peach-pink-cream-leaves-stunning', 'ETSY-0060', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/25a844/6149260943/il_fullxfull.6149260943_ddqv.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 10\" - 12\" tall. Another beautiful cultivar in the Ghost Series! Like its siblings, \'Uncle Ghost\' is celebrated for its spectacular reticulated variegation—meaning the primary veins of the leaf remain a sharp, contrasting color while the tissue between them changes dramatically throughout the seasons.\nThe Golden Rule for Ghost Maples: Protection from the afternoon sun is non-negotiable. Because the variegated sections have very little chlorophyll, hot, direct afternoon sunlight will quickly scorch the leaf margins.\n\nSpring: Leaves emerge in a striking flush of bright rose-pink, peach, or soft crimson. The inner leaf tissue quickly transitions into a cream or amber wash, while the prominent emerald or lime-green veins remain deeply etched.\n\nSummer: The bright pinks mature into olive-green and soft cream tones with red-purple highlights on the tips, giving the entire canopy an ethereal, hazy appearance.\n\nFall: The tree puts on a classic, fiery finale, shifting to bright golden-yellows, oranges, and deep crimsons.\n\nSunlight: Give it morning sun and afternoon shade (or bright, dappled woodland light). This keeps the delicate cream and pink tones from burning while ensuring the colors stay vibrant.\nSoil: Plant in rich, organic, well-draining soil that is slightly acidic (pH\\ 5.5 - 6.5). Like all Japanese maples, they absolutely hate \"wet feet\" and will quickly decline in saturated or heavy clay soils.\nWatering: Maintain consistent, even moisture. Deeply water once or twice a week, increasing the frequency during dry summer spells. Applying a thick layer of organic mulch around the root zone helps regulate temperature and conserve moisture (just keep it a couple of inches away from the trunk).\n\nCommon Name: \'Uncle Ghost\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum \nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Full sun/part sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 6\' to 10\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 10\" - 12\" tall.', '[\"Hard To Find Tree\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Reticulated Leaves\",\"Contrasting Colors\",\"Brilliant Fall Color\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Ghost Series\",\"Ornamental Tree\",\"Small Garden Space\",\"Patio Garden\",\"Woodland Garden\",\"Low Maintenance\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 2, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:11', '2026-06-24 16:09:11'),
(333, 'Japanese Maple \'Shoryu No Tsume\' Acer sieboldianum Live Grafted Tree Claw Of The Dragon Green Leaves Cold Hardy---Unique!!', 'japanese-maple-shoryu-no-tsume-acer-sieboldianum-live-grafted-tree-claw-of-the-dragon-green-leaves-cold-hardy-unique', 'ETSY-0061', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/6cfb2b/6107892760/il_fullxfull.6107892760_5nyy.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 10\" - 12\" tall. A really unique cold hardy cultivar! This tree is a highly unique and strikingly sculptural cultivar. Its name beautifully translates to \"Claw of the Dragon,\" which perfectly describes the appearance of its distinctive foliage. The leaves are heavily divided with exceptionally narrow, elongated, and slightly twisted lobes. This claw- or talon-like appearance gives the tree an unmatched fine texture in the garden.\n\nSpring: Emerges a bright, crisp green, occasionally sporting a subtle red tint along the margins.  \nSummer: Matures into a rich, deep emerald green.\nFall: Puts on a dramatic finale, transforming into brilliant, fiery shades of crimson red and neon orange.\n\nGrowth Habit: It develops an upright, spreading form with graceful, slightly arching branches. It typically reaches a mature height of 10 to 12 feet and a width of 4 to 6 feet over 10–15 years, making it an excellent focal specimen for smaller landscapes.\n\nSun Exposure: Thrives in full sun to partial shade. In hotter southern climates (Zones 8 and 9), giving it morning sun and protecting it from harsh afternoon rays will prevent leaf scorch.  \n\nSoil & Water: Prefers moist, rich, well-draining, and slightly acidic soil. It also exhibits better humidity tolerance than many traditional palmatum varieties.\n\nCommon Name: \'Shoryu No Tsume\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer sieboldianum \nHardiness Zones: 4 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Full sun/part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 10\' to 12\' tall and 4\' to 6\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 10\" - 12\" tall.', '[\"Specimen Tree\",\"Woodland Garden\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Brilliant Fall Color\",\"Interesting Leaves\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Cold Hardy Tree\",\"Street Tree\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Unique Leaf Shape\",\"Dragon Claw\",\"Upright Growth\",\"Small Garden Space\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 2, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:12', '2026-06-24 16:09:12');
