(334, 'Japanese Maple \'Scarlet Princess\' Acer palmatum dissectum Live Grafted Tree Dwarf Weeping Laceleaf Red Leaves---Stunning!!', 'japanese-maple-scarlet-princess-acer-palmatum-dissectum-live-grafted-tree-dwarf-weeping-laceleaf-red-leaves-stunning', 'ETSY-0062', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/2ce1f7/5407510470/il_fullxfull.5407510470_feh5.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted plant that is 8\" - 10\" tall. This grafted cultivar is an exceptional, super-dwarf laceleaf Japanese maple that redefines compact garden design. The \'daughter\" of the Crimson Queen it inherits her mother\'s best traits but stays roughly half the size. Because of its petite footprint and striking texture, \'Scarlet Princess\' is a premier choice for container gardening, patio accents, rock gardens, small conifer beds, and bonsai.\n\nSpring: Flushes out early with striking, vibrant pinkish-red to bright orange-red tones. \n Summer: Matures into a rich, deep bronze-red or burgundy. It stays impressively heat-tolerant, and new bright red leaves continue to pop on the tips all summer long.  \nFall: True to its name, it wraps up the season with a brilliant, glowing display of fiery scarlet-red.\n\nGrowth Habit: A tightly mounding, dense, and weeping habit. It often starts out with slightly ascending branches before gracefully cascading down, creating a compact ball or structural umbrella shape.  \nSize at Maturity: Extremely slow-growing. It generally reaches only 2 to 3 feet tall and wide in 10 years, making it arguably the smallest red laceleaf variety in existence.\n\nCommon Name: \'Scarlet Princess\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum dissectum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Morning sun/Afternoon Shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 2\' to 3\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted plant that is 8\" - 10\" tall.', '[\"Small Space\",\"Bonsai Tree\",\"Container Plant\",\"Fairy Garden\",\"Compact Form\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Spring Color\",\"Fall Color\",\"Fine Textured Leaves\",\"Rock Garden\",\"Accent Plant\",\"Specimen Tree\",\"Weeping Tree\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 3, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:12', '2026-06-24 16:09:12'),
(335, 'Japanese Maple \'Strawberry Spring\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Pink Green Reticulated Leaves---Gorgeous!!', 'japanese-maple-strawberry-spring-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-pink-green-reticulated-leaves-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0063', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/69f17e/7094227977/il_fullxfull.7094227977_rjz6.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 8\" - 10\" tall. This grafted tree is a relatively new and highly sought-after reticulated Japanese maple cultivar, it belongs to what collectors often call the \"New Ghost\" lineage. It grows in an upright and moderately compact habit.\n\nSpring: Leaves emerge a bright strawberry or salmony pink with a creamy backdrop. Prominent, dark green veins map intricately across the surface, creating a striking \"reticulated\" (webbed) look.  \nSummer: The intense pink tones gradually transition to a soft, creamy white or light green, though flush new growth in summer will often bring back splashes of that bright pink against the darker mature leaves.  \nFall: The tree puts on a vibrant finale, turning a rich mix of golden yellows, brilliant oranges, and deep rusty reds.\n\nBecause of its unique, delicate variegation, \'Strawberry Spring\' requires intentional placement to avoid leaf scorch:  \nSunlight: Thrives best with morning sun and afternoon shade. Protection from the intense afternoon sun is critical to preserving the bright pink tones and preventing the creamy edges from burning, especially in hot or southern climates. \nSoil & Water: Prefers moist, well-draining, slightly acidic soil. Consistent watering is necessary while the tree establishes its root system. It does not tolerate waterlogged, soggy roots.  \nLandscape Use: Due to its compact size, it makes an excellent focal point for smaller gardens, rock gardens, or as a spectacular specimen plant in large containers.  \n\nCommon Name: \'Strawberry Spring\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Morning sun/Afternoon shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 6\' to 8\' tall and 4\' to 6\' wide \nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 8\" - 10\" tall.', '[\"Japanese Maples\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Brilliant Fall Color\",\"Red Fall Leaves\",\"Orange Fall Leaves\",\"Reticulated Leaves\",\"Small Garden Space\",\"Rock Garden\",\"Ornamental Tree\",\"Specimen Tree\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 2, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:12', '2026-06-24 16:09:12'),
(336, 'Dwarf Korean Lilac \'Palibin\' Syringa meyeri Live Plant Fragrant Light Purple Flowers---Beautiful!!', 'dwarf-korean-lilac-palibin-syringa-meyeri-live-plant-fragrant-light-purple-flowers-beautiful', 'ETSY-0064', 'simple', 17, NULL, 'Lilacs', 24.85, NULL, 14.91, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/310e48/3881737466/il_fullxfull.3881737466_tgey.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA!!\n***WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES***\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live plant that is 6\" - 10\" tall and multi-branched.  This beautiful plant is a dwarf spreading variety that has reddish purple buds that open into light purple fragrant and showy flowers in mid Spring. These make a great informal hedge when planted in groups and is perfect for a cutting garden!\n\nCommon Name: \'Palibin\' Dwarf Korean Lilac\nBotanical Name: Syringa meyeri\nHardiness Zones: 3 - 7\nBloom Time: Spring\nSunlight: Full sun or part sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 4\' to 6\' tall and 5\' to 7\' wide\nBloom Color: Light purple\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live plant that is 6\" - 10\" tall and multi-branched.', '[\"Long Bloom Time\",\"Cut Flower\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Repeat Flowers\",\"Mass Planting\",\"Cutting Garden\",\"Urban Garden\",\"Fragrant Flowers\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Rustic Garden\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Attracts Pollinators\",\"Informal Hedge\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 6, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:12', '2026-06-24 16:09:12'),
(337, 'Rhododendron \'Milky Way\' Live Plant Evergreen Shrub White Flower Clusters---Gorgeous!!', 'rhododendron-milky-way-live-plant-evergreen-shrub-white-flower-clusters-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0065', 'simple', 15, NULL, 'Evergreen Shrubs', 24.90, NULL, 14.94, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/257d05/8024359050/il_fullxfull.8024359050_keu8.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live plant that is 6\" - 8\" tall and growing! This broadleaf evergreen Rhodie variety is a real looker! In Spring, they are covered with beautiful trumpet shaped flower clusters that are white in color! The flower colors make a great contrast against the glossy green leaves! This is a very cold hardy variety! Since it\'s an evergreen, you get year round visual interest!!\n\nCommon Name: \'Milky Way\' Rhododendron\nBotanical Name: Rhododendron diversipilosum\nHardiness Zones: 3 - 9\nBloom Time: Mid Spring or early Summer\nSunlight: Full sun/part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 3\' tall and 4\' wide\nBloom Color: White\nEvergreen or Deciduous: Evergreen', '1 live plant that is 6\" - 8\" tall and growing! This broadleaf evergreen Rhodie variety is a real looker! In Spring, they are covered with beautiful trumpet shaped flower clusters that are white in color! The flower color...', '[\"Evergreen Shrub\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Hummingbirds Love\",\"Attracts Pollinators\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Small Garden Space\",\"Woodland Garden\",\"Broadleaf Shrub\",\"Dense Shrub\",\"Benefits Birds\",\"Disease Resistant\",\"Flowering Hedge\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 3, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16: