mal Hedge\",\"Container Plant\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 3, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:13', '2026-06-24 16:09:13'),
(340, 'Mountain Laurel \'Minuet\' Kalmia latifolia Live Plant Evergreen Shrub Pink Buds White & Maroon Flowers---Stunning!!', 'mountain-laurel-minuet-kalmia-latifolia-live-plant-evergreen-shrub-pink-buds-white-maroon-flowers-stunning', 'ETSY-0068', 'simple', 15, NULL, 'Evergreen Shrubs', 34.20, NULL, 20.52, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/1c66b9/6534210943/il_fullxfull.6534210943_chim.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live plant that is 6\" - 8\" tall ! Mountain Laurels are hard to find!! In late Spring/early Summer, it has pink buds that open up into white flowers with a maroon band around the inside edge! It has a long bloom time, so you can enjoy gorgeous flowers for quite a while! It\'s compact size makes it a great choice for containers too!!\n\nCommon Name: \'Minuet\' Mountain Laurel\nBotanical Name: Kalmia latifolia\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: Late Spring/early Summer \nSunlight: Part sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 3\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: White with maroon band\nEvergreen or Deciduous: Evergreen', '1 live plant that is 6\" - 8\" tall ! Mountain Laurels are hard to find!! In late Spring/early Summer, it has pink buds that open up into white flowers with a maroon band around the inside edge! It has a long bloom time, s...', '[\"Evergreen Shrub\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Long Bloom Time\",\"Small Garden Space\",\"Border Plant\",\"Container Garden\",\"Cut Flowers\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Attracts Butterflies\",\"Bee Friendly\",\"Compact Shape\",\"Low Informal Hedge\",\"Rabbit Resistant\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 2, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:13', '2026-06-24 16:09:13'),
(341, 'Japanese Maple \'Tsuma Gaki\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Red Tipped Yellow Green Leaves---WOW!!', 'japanese-maple-tsuma-gaki-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-red-tipped-yellow-green-leaves-wow', 'ETSY-0069', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/18ed5e/5418569433/il_fullxfull.5418569433_axbi.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live plant that is 8\" - 10\" tall. This grafted variety definitely makes a statement in your landscape! It is one of the most distinctive and highly prized Japanese maple cultivars, specifically famous for its dramatic spring show. The name translates beautifully to \"red fingernails\" or \"painted fingernails,\" which perfectly describes how the leaves look when they emerge.\n\nThe Spring Show: When the deeply divided leaves unfurl in spring, they emerge a soft, pale chartreuse or yellowish-green. The tips and edges of each lobe are sharply dipped in a vivid, contrasting crimson-red—giving it that iconic \"painted fingernail\" look.\n\nSummer Transition: As the season progresses into summer, the bright red tips soften, and the entire leaf matures into a rich, solid green.\n\nFall Color: In autumn, the tree transitions again, turning brilliant shades of crimson, orange, and bright yellow.\n\nSize & Shape: It is a slow-growing, compact dwarf to semi-dwarf shrub or small tree. It typically reaches about 6 to 8 feet tall and wide after 10 years, making it an excellent choice for smaller gardens, containers, or as a focal point near a patio.\n\nLight: Best planted in dappled shade or morning sun with afternoon protection. Intense, direct afternoon sun can scorch the delicate pale-yellow spring foliage.\n\nSoil: Prefers moist, well-draining, slightly acidic soil. Like most Japanese maples, it does not tolerate soggy roots or heavy clay well.\n\nProtection: Because its early spring growth is so spectacular, try to plant it in a spot sheltered from harsh, drying winds that can fray the new leaves.\n\nCommon Name: \'Tsuma Gaki\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Full sun/part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 6\' to 8\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live plant that is 8\" - 10\" tall.', '[\"Japanese Maple\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Low Maintanence\",\"Fall Color\",\"Bright Colors\",\"Chartreuse Leaves\",\"Specimen Plant\",\"Upright Growth\",\"Rounded Shape\",\"Broadleaf Tree\",\"Dwarf Tree\",\"Small Tree\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 2, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:14', '2026-06-24 16:09:14'),
(342, 'Japanese Maple \'Kumoi Nishiki\' Grafted Tree, Variegated Cold-Tolerant Leaves', 'japanese-maple-kumoi-nishiki-grafted-tree-variegated-cold-tolerant-leaves', 'ETSY-0070', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/05450b/5829382826/il_fullxfull.5829382826_my2l.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 8\" - 10\" tall. Another beautiful variety with variegated leaves, plus it\'s cold tolerant! It is a highly sought-after, collectable Japanese maple (Acer palmatum) famous for its striking, multi-colored variegation. The name translates beautifully from Japanese as \"brocade clouds,\" which perfectly captures the mottled, cloud-like patterns on its leaves. Unlike some variegated maples that feature distinct borders or blocks of color, \'Kumoi nishiki\' is known for its freckled, speckled, and mottled variegation. No two leaves are exactly alike.\n\nSize: It is a moderate, upright grower, typically reaching 8 to 12 feet tall and about 6 to 8 feet wide over 10 to 15 years.\n\nShape: It forms a dense, well-branched, small tree or large shrub with a rounded canopy.\n\nContainers & Small Gardens: Because of its compact, slow-to-moderate growth rate, it makes a phenomenal focal point for small courtyards, Japanese-style gardens, or as a long-term container specimen.\n\nSpring: Leaves emerge with a vibrant blend of soft green, creamy white, and pale yellow, often heavily flushed with bright pink or soft orange highlights on the tips.\n\nSummer: The variegation matures into a crisp green-and-white flecked pattern. The variegation holds up remarkably well in summer compared to other cultivars, provided it doesn\'t get scorched.\n\nAutumn: The tree puts on a dramatic finale, transforming into rich shades of orange, yellow, and deep crimson. The white variegated spots often turn a brilliant orange-pink color.\n\nLight: Give it dappled shade or morning sun with afternoon protection. Too much direct, harsh afternoon sun will scorch the delicate white parts of the leaves. Too much deep shade, and you will lose that brilliant mottled variegation, causing the leaves to revert to a solid, dull green.\n\nSoil: Like most Japanese maples, it thrives in moist, rich, slightly acidic, and exceptionally well-drained soil. They hate having \"wet feet\" (standing water).\n\nMulching: Apply a shallow layer of mulch around the base to keep the shallow root system cool and retain moisture during hot summer spells.\n\nCommon Name: \'Kumoi Nishiki\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum\nHardiness Zones: 4 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Part sun/part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 8\' to 12\' tall and 6\' to 8\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 8\" - 10\" tall.', '[\"Variegated Leaves\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Cold Hardy Tree\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Brilliant Color\",\"Asian Garden\",\"Specimen Tree\",\"Fall Color\",\"Visual Interest\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Full Moon Maple\",\"Speckled Leaves\",\"Upright Growth\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 2, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:14', '2026-06-24 16:09:14'),
(343, 'Hardy Hibiscus moscheutos \'Luna Rose\' Perennial Live Plant Large Pink Flowers--Gorgeous!!', 'hardy-hibiscus-moscheutos-luna-rose-perennial-live-plant-large-pink-flowers-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0071', 'simple', 9, NULL, 'Roses', 24.75, NULL, 14.85, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/48e24e/3974892805/il_fullxfull.3974892805_4jr8.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live plant that is 10\"- 12\" tall and growing! This beautiful variety comes back year after year and produce large rose pink flowers in Summer and Fall...did I say the flowers are huge? The flowers measure a whopping 8\" across! The plant will die back to the ground in Winter and can be a little slow to make an appearance in Spring, but it\'s well worth the wait! Make your landscape the talk of the neighborhood with these beauties!\n\nCommon Name: \'Luna Rose\' Hardy Hibiscus\nBotanical Name: Hibiscus moscheutos\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: Summer to Fall\nSunlight: Full sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 2\' to 3\' tall and 1\' to 2\' wide\nBloom Color: Rose pink\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Herbaceous perennial that dies back to the ground in Winter', '1 live plant that is 10\"- 12\" tall and growing! This beautiful variety comes back year after year and produce large rose pink flowers in Summer and Fall.', '[\"Large Flower\",\"Rose Pink Flower\",\"Easy Care\",\"Urban Garden\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Pollinator Plant\",\"Attracts Butterflies\",\"Tropical Look\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Hummingbirds Love\",\"Container Plant\",\"Border Plant\",\"Specimen Plant\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 7, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:14', '2026-06-24 16:09:14'),
(344, 'Seiun Kaku Dwarf Japanese Maple Grafted Tree, Great for Bonsai', 'seiun-kaku-dwarf-japanese-maple-grafted-tree-great-for-bonsai', 'ETSY-0072', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/955d85/6006744943/il_fullxfull.6006744943_f3pm.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 4\"- 6\" tall. This beautiful dwarf variety is a rare and striking dwarf-to-semi-dwarf Japanese maple cultivar. Its poetic name translates beautifully to \"blue-green palace in the clouds\" (or \"tower in the sky\"), which perfectly describes the unique, layered cloud-like structural habit it forms as it matures.\nIf you are familiar with the famous \'Mikawa yatsubusa\' cultivar, \'Seiun kaku\' shares a very similar look with closely set, overlapping leaves that stack like shingles on a roof. However, it grows faster and creates a slightly more open, upright, and airy silhouette.\n\nSpring: Leaves emerge a bright chartreuse or yellow-green, contrasted sharply by prominent red stems (petioles).  Summer: The foliage matures into a crisp, deep medium green.\nFall: It puts on an absolute show, shifting into brilliant, electric shades of orange and fiery deep red.\n\nSize & Growth Habit: It typically reaches about 5 to 6 feet tall in 10 years, eventually topping out around 8 to 10 feet at full maturity with a matching spread. The main structural branches tend to grow horizontally, while the smaller leaf-bearing twigs point vertically, building that signature \"layered palace\" appearance.  \nBest Uses: Because of its compact size, dense texture, and exceptional natural architecture, it is a premier choice for bonsai artists, patio containers, or as a focal specimen in small urban gardens.\n\nLight: Prefers dappled or morning sun with afternoon shade. In cooler northern zones, it can handle more sun, but hot afternoon rays in the south can scorch its dense leaf clusters.  \nSoil & Water: Requires moist, highly organic, and impeccably well-drained soil. Like most Japanese maples, it hates sitting in stagnant, soggy dirt.\n\nCommon Name: \'Seiun Kaku\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 8\' to 10\' tall and 5\' to 6\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 4\"- 6\" tall.', '[\"Japanese Maple\",\"Rare Tree\",\"East To Grow\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Small Spaces\",\"Specimen Tree\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Asian Garden\",\"Dwarf Tree\",\"Container Plant\",\"Bonsai\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 4, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:15', '2026-06-24 16:09:15'),
(345, 'Weigela Florida \'Minuet\' Live Plant Perennial Shrub Fragrant Rosy Pink Flowers Attracts Pollinators---Gorgeous!!', 'weigela-florida-minuet-live-plant-perennial-shrub-fragrant-rosy-pink-flowers-attracts-pollinators-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0073', 'simple', 7, NULL, 'Flowering Shrubs', 20.45, NULL, 12.27, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/c93601/4203886275/il_fullxfull.4203886275_tptr.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live plant that is 6\"- 8\" tall and multi-branched. This plant will definitely give your garden a WOW factor!! It explodes with fragrant rosy pink trumpet shaped flowers in Spring that Hummingbirds, butterflies and bees absolutely love! The leaves are purple tinged that gives this plant even more visual interest! These are a great option to use as either a specimen plant or plant a bunch for a fabulous hedge!! \n\nCommon Name: \'Minuet\' Weigela\nBotanical Name: Weigela florida\nHardiness Zones: 4 - 8\nBloom Time: Spring\nSunlight: Full sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 3\' tall and 5\' wide\nBloom Color: Rose pink\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live plant that is 6\"- 8\" tall and multi-branched.', '[\"Low Maintenance\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Spring Flowers\",\"Attracts Butterflies\",\"Urban Garden\",\"Rustic Garden\",\"Pollinator Plant\",\"Fragrant Flowers\",\"Hedge Plant\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Specimen Plant\",\"Container Plant\",\"Hummingbirds Love\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 15, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:15', '2026-06-24 16:09:15'),
(346, 'Thornless Blackberry \"Triple Crown\" Live Starter Plant Perennial Large Edible Fruit---Yum!!', 'thornless-blackberry-triple-crown-live-starter-plant-perennial-large-edible-fruit-yum', 'ETSY-0074', 'simple', 3, NULL, 'Perennials', 20.40, NULL, 12.24, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/6dc77b/4081306569/il_fullxfull.4081306569_8d9n.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live STARTER plant that is 4\"- 6\" tall and multi-branched. This beautiful variety is thornless, so your fingers will thank you! It is named for its three attributes: flavor, productivity and flavor. It has strong canes and bears large and super tasty berries in late Summer. These plants can be trellised or pruned, whichever way you like!!\n\nCommon Name: \"Triple Crown\" Thornless Blackberry\nBotanical Name: Rubus fruticosus\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: Late Summer \nSunlight: Full sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: Keep pruned to 5\' to 6\' tall \nBloom Color: White\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live STARTER plant that is 4\"- 6\" tall and multi-branched.', '[\"Pollinator\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Spring Flowers\",\"Summer Fruit\",\"Vigorous\",\"Large Fruit\",\"Semi-Upright\",\"Thornless\",\"Productive\",\"Sturdy Canes\",\"Urban Garden\",\"Woodland Garden\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 2, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:15', '2026-06-24 16:09:15'),
(347, 'Abelia x grandiflora \'Edward Goucher\' Live Starter Plant Flowering Shrub Pink Flowers---Gorgeous!!', 'abelia-x-grandiflora-edward-goucher-live-starter-plant-flowering-shrub-pink-flowers-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0075', 'simple', 3, NULL, 'Perennials', 16.85, NULL, 10.11, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/2aee61/4883832646/il_fullxfull.4883832646_1d5g.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n***WE DO NOT SHIP TO PO BOXES***\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF WHAT YOU WILL RECEIVE!!\n\nThis listing is for 1 live starter plant that is 3\"- 5\" tall, growing in a 2 1/2\" pot. This beautiful variety has glossy green leaves, is semi-evergreen and has gorgeous bell-shaped lilac pink flowers in Summer! The flowering continues on its arching branches into Fall to really make a statement! Easy to grow and attracts all of your favorite pollinators too!!\n\nCommon Name: \'Edward Goucher\' Abelia\nBotanical Name: Abelia x grandiflora\nHardiness Zones: 6 - 9\nBloom Time: Summer to Fall\nSunlight: Full sun/part sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 4\' to 6\' tall wide\nBloom Color: Pink\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Semi-evergreen', '1 live starter plant that is 3\"- 5\" tall, growing in a 2 1/2\" pot.', '[\"Low Maintenance\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Summer Flowers\",\"Fall Flowers\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Border Planting\",\"Informal Hedge\",\"Arching Branches\",\"Attracts Pollinators\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Hummingbirds Love\",\"Dramatic Fall Color\",\"Starter Plant\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 5, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:15', '2026-06-24 16:09:15'),
(348, 'French Pink Pussy Willow Live Starter Plant Silvery Pale Pink Catkins---Gorgeous!!', 'french-pink-pussy-willow-live-starter-plant-silvery-pale-pink-catkins-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0076', 'simple', 12, NULL, 'Willows', 16.85, NULL, 10.11, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/71cb80/4435371325/il_fullxfull.4435371325_if09.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA!!\nWE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF WHAT YOU WILL RECEIVE!\n\nThis listing is for 1 live starter plant that is 3\" - 6\" tall! This is a very pretty variety!! In Spring, it has these beautiful fuzzy pale pink catkins that really stand out in your landscape! These make a wonderful small tree or shrub and you can cut the branches in Winter and force them indoors...great for cut flower arrangements too!!\n\nCommon Name: French Pink Pussy Willow\nBotanical Name: Salix caprea\nHardiness Zones: 4 - 8\nBloom Time: Spring\nSunlight: Full sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 10\' to 15\' tall and 10\' to 12\' wide\nBloom Color: Light pink\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live starter plant that is 3\" - 6\" tall! This is a very pretty variety!! In Spring, it has these beautiful fuzzy pale pink catkins that really stand out in your landscape! These make a wonderful small tree or shrub and...', '[\"Low Maintenance\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Spring Flowers\",\"Force Branches\",\"Fast Growing\",\"Deer Resistant\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Specimen Plant\",\"Erosion Control\",\"Dried Flowers\",\"Early Blooming\",\"Informal Hedge\",\"Starter Plant\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 20, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:16', '2026-06-24 16:09:16'),
(349, 'Black Pussy Willow StarterPlant 2 1/2\" pot. Perennial Shrub Unique Black Catkins---Gorgeous!!', 'black-pussy-willow-starterplant-2-12-pot-perennial-shrub-unique-black-catkins-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0077', 'simple', 12, NULL, 'Willows', 16.85, NULL, 10.11, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/1efab2/7977052769/il_fullxfull.7977052769_1t0y.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, IDAHO, HAWAII AND NEVADA\n***WE DO NOT SHIP TO PO BOXES***\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live starter plant that is 3\"- 5\" tall! This is truly a unique shrub!! In early Spring, it will produce deep purple/black catkins with red anthers before the leaves emerge...it really puts on a show! The red anthers mature to yellow which adds to it\'s visual interest. You can cut this shrub back to the ground every 3-5 years if it gest too tall, or just keep it pruned to your desired height. It\'s a bushy shrub that makes a great ornamental shrub with its arching branches. If you want something different, this is the one to get!!\n\nCommon Name: Black Pussy Willow\nBotanical Name: Salix gracilistyla \'Melanostachys\'\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 8\nBloom Time: Early Spring\nSunlight: Full sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 6\' - 10\' tall and  wide\nBloom Color: Deep purple/black\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live starter plant that is 3\"- 5\" tall! This is truly a unique shrub!! In early Spring, it will produce deep purple/black catkins with red anthers before the leaves emerge.', '[\"Low Maintenance\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Spring Flowers\",\"Cut Flowers\",\"Urban Garden\",\"Flower Beds\",\"Specimen Plant\",\"Mass Planting\",\"Arching Habit\",\"Unique Plant\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Hedge Plant\",\"Ornamental Shrub\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 20, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:16', '2026-06-24 16:09:16'),
(350, 'Knockout Miniature Rose \'Petite\' Starter Plant Semi-Double Flowers---Beautiful!!', 'knockout-miniature-rose-petite-starter-plant-semi-double-flowers-beautiful', 'ETSY-0078', 'simple', 9, NULL, 'Roses', 25.90, NULL, 15.54, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/e0da65/8001676178/il_fullxfull.8001676178_2p93.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live starter plant that is 3\" - 6\" tall and growing quickly in a quart pot! This variety is a highly disease-resistant, low maintenance shrub rose. It\'s unique miniature size makes it perfect for small places and containers. It has double-petaled red flowers that bloom continuously from spring until frost and don\'t require deadheading!!\n\nCommon Name: \'Petite\'  Knockout Rose\nBotanical Name: Rosa \'Meibenbino\' PP 30,811\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 10\nBloom Time: Spring, Summer, Fall\nSunlight: Full sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 18\" tall and wide\nBloom Color: Fire Engine red\nEvergreen or Deciduous: Deciduous', '1 live starter plant that is 3\" - 6\" tall and growing quickly in a quart pot! This variety is a highly disease-resistant, low maintenance shrub rose.', '[\"Shrub Rose\",\"Long Bloom Time\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Cut Flowers\",\"Container Garden\",\"Garden Border\",\"Flowering Hedge\",\"Bushy Rose\",\"Fast Growing\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Self Deadheading\",\"Disease Resistant\",\"Miniature\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 3, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:16', '2026-06-24 16:09:16'),
(351, 'Frilly Willy Japanese Maple Grafted Tree, Unique Lace Type Leaves---Gorgeous!!', 'frilly-willy-japanese-maple-grafted-tree-unique-lace-type-leaves-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0079', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/4318c5/7856966030/il_fullxfull.7856966030_l4w3.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 8\"- 10\" tall. This grafted cultivar is relatively new! If you love the delicate look of a laceleaf (dissectum type) but want the structured habit of an upright tree rather than a weeping mound, \'Frilly Willy\' hits the sweet spot. It gets its fun name from its deeply shredded, slender leaves with heavily serrated edges that give the entire canopy a distinct, fine-textured, \"frilly\" appearance.\n\nGrowth Habit: Dwarf, upright shrub or small tree. It stands apart from standard laceleafs because it reaches skyward rather than weeping downward.\nFoliage Lifecycle: Emerges light green with a soft pink blush in spring, matures to a solid medium green for summer, and explodes into vibrant flashes of orange and bright red in autumn.\nMature Size: Typically reaches 5 to 10 feet tall and 3 to 6 feet wide over 10 to 15 years, making it an exceptional compact option for small gardens or containers.\n\nLight: Thrives in morning sun with afternoon shade, or dappled/filtered light.  \n\nSoil & Water: Prefers rich, acidic, well-draining soil with regular moisture. It is noted for having slightly better humidity tolerance than some of the older, delicate laceleaf varieties.\n\nCommon Name: \'Frilly Willy\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Morning Sun/Afternoon Shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 5\' to 10\' tall and 3\' to 6\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 8\"- 10\" tall.', '[\"Japanese Maple\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Brilliant Fall Color\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Hard To Find Tree\",\"Serrated Leaves\",\"Lacy Leaves\",\"Adds Texture\",\"Orange Fall Color\",\"Red Fall Color\",\"Woodland Garden\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 3, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:16', '2026-06-24 16:09:16'),
(352, 'Japanese Maple \'Daidai haru\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Rare Orange Spring Leaves---Gorgeous!!', 'japanese-maple-daidai-haru-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-rare-orange-spring-leaves-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0080', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/048b23/6079152654/il_fullxfull.6079152654_cni5.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 10\" - 12\" tall. This tree is a spectacular and relatively rare Acer palmatum cultivar that lives up to its name. If you love dynamic, changing foliage, this one is an absolute showstopper.\n\'Daidai haru\' has a classic, upright growth habit with delicate, deeply divided 5-to-7-lobed leaves. It is generally considered a semi-dwarf to medium-sized tree, making it exceptionally versatile:\n\n10-Year Height: Expect it to reach around 6 to 8 feet tall.\n\nLandscape Use: Because of its manageable size, it excels as a focal point in small gardens, large containers, or as a vibrant contrast plant nestled among darker evergreens.\n\nSpring: This is its peak performance window. The new leaves emerge in a brilliant, luminous shade of bright yellow-green to chartreuse, strongly edged in a soft, glowing orange-pink or peach margin.\n\nSummer: As the season progresses, the vivid chartreuse tones mellow out into a more stable, clean light green.\n\nAutumn: It finishes the year strong, shifting into rich, warm tones of deep orange and fiery red before shedding its leaves.\n\nLike many of the lighter-colored, yellow-gold maples, placement is key to keeping the foliage pristine:\n\nSunlight: It thrives best in dappled shade or morning sun with afternoon protection. Too much harsh afternoon sun can scorch the delicate spring edges, while too much dense shade will cause the bright orange-yellow colors to fade to a plain green prematurely.\n\nSoil: Requires well-drained, acidic soil that stays consistently moist but never waterlogged.\n\nCommon Name: \'Daidai haru\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum \nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Full sun/part sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 6\' to 8\' tall and 4\' to 6\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 10\" - 12\" tall.', '[\"Rare Tree\",\"All Season Interest\",\"Striped Bark\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Brilliant Fall Color\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Woodland Garden\",\"Slow Growing\",\"Interesting Bark\",\"Unusual Leaves\",\"Contrasting Colors\",\"Asian Garden\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 2, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:17', '2026-06-24 16:09:17'),
(353, 'Japanese Maple \'Anne Irene\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Rare Yellow Red Border Leaves---Unique Leaf Shape!!', 'japanese-maple-anne-irene-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-rare-yellow-red-border-leaves-unique-leaf-shape', 'ETSY-0081', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/e5002d/5435183927/il_fullxfull.5435183927_gylc.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 8\"- 10\" tall. This is another fabulous cultivar is a striking, relatively rare Japanese maple cultivar that stands out for its intensely bright, chartreuse-to-yellow foliage and excellent sun tolerance compared to other yellow maples. It\'s an upright, slow-to-moderate grower that acts as a brilliant focal point in a garden landscape. The intense neon-yellow of the \'Anne Irene\' leaves creates a stunning, high-contrast visual pop against darker backdrops.\n\nSpring: Leaves emerge a vibrant lime green to bright chartreuse, often showing a distinct, delicate reddish-pink margin along the serrated edges of the lobes.\n\nSummer: The foliage matures into a solid, luminous golden-yellow. Unlike many yellow cultivars (like \'Aureum\') which easily scorch in direct sunlight, \'Anne Irene\' holds its golden color exceptionally well without burning, provided it gets adequate moisture.\n\nAutumn: The tree transitions into deep, fiery tones of orange and crimson red.\n\nForm: Upright, multi-branched, and compact. It forms a dense, neat structure naturally.\nHeight: Reaches roughly 8 to 10 feet tall over 10 years, eventually maturing around 12 to 15 feet.\nWidth: Generally spreads about 6 to 8 feet wide, maintaining a slightly narrower profile than its height.\nLeaf Shape: Classic palmate shape with 5 to 7 deeply divided, sharply serrated lobes.\n\nLight: Performs best in full sun to partial shade. To get the absolute best yellow summer color, it needs a good amount of sunlight, but afternoon dappled shade is highly beneficial in exceptionally hot climates.\n\nSoil: Requires well-draining, moist, acidic soil rich in organic matter. Like most Japanese maples, it hates sitting in waterlogged soil, which can lead to root rot.\n\nWatering: Regular watering is essential, especially during the hot summer months or when establishing its root system.\n\nContainers: Because of its slower growth rate and compact upright habit, it makes an excellent candidate for large patio containers or smaller garden spaces.\n\nCommon Name: \'Anne Irene\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 8\' to 10\' tall and 6\' to 8\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 8\"- 10\" tall.', '[\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Spring Color\",\"Fall Color\",\"Rare Tree\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Asian Garden\",\"Frilly Edge Leaves\",\"Broadleaf Tree\",\"Color Contrast\",\"Dwarf Tree\",\"Small Space\",\"Container Tree\",\"Patio Garden\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 3, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:17', '2026-06-24 16:09:17');
