(354, 'Japanese Maple \'Germaine\'s Gyration\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Weeping Green Leaves Twisting Branches---Unique!!', 'japanese-maple-germaines-gyration-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-weeping-green-leaves-twisting-branches-unique', 'ETSY-0082', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/5c9523/6121604964/il_fullxfull.6121604964_383y.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 8\"- 10\" tall. This weeping cultivar is definitely different! Unlike many other lace-leaf maples that have a more traditional, uniform cascading habit, the Germaine\'s Gyration gets its name from its branches that seem to swirl, twist, and \"gyrate\" as they grow. This creates a really sculptural, intricate look, especially in winter when the leaves have dropped and you can see the architecture of the branches.\n\nForm: A broad, semi-weeping mound. It is generally more vigorous and faster-growing than many other delicate dissectum varieties.  \nFoliage: It features finely dissected (lace-like) green leaves that often emerge with a subtle peach or bronze tint in the spring.  \nFall Color: You’ll typically see a beautiful transition into golden yellows, oranges, and occasionally red as the temperatures drop.  \nSize: It usually reaches about 6–8 feet in height and 8–12 feet in width, making it a great specimen plant for a garden bed or a large container.  \nSun Tolerance: It is known to be quite durable and can handle more sun than some of the more sensitive red lace-leaf varieties, though it still appreciates some protection during the hottest part of the day in warmer climates \n\nCommon Name: \'Germaine\'s Gyration\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum \nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Part sun/part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 6\' to 8\' tall and 10\' to 12\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 8\"- 10\" tall.', '[\"Fast Growing\",\"Weeping Tree\",\"Unusual Branches\",\"Unique Tree\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Brilliant Fall Color\",\"Specimen Tree\",\"Ornamental Tree\",\"Woodland Garden\",\"Vigorous Growth\",\"Contorted Branches\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 3, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:17', '2026-06-24 16:09:17'),
(355, 'Japanese Maple \'Winter Flame\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Dwarf Coral Bark Green Leaves---Stunning!!', 'japanese-maple-winter-flame-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-dwarf-coral-bark-green-leaves-stunning', 'ETSY-0083', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/0be564/5877186589/il_fullxfull.5877186589_o28c.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 6\"- 8\" tall. This variety is a phenomenal dwarf coral-bark Japanese maple. If you love the classic, brilliant red winter branches of \'Sango kaku\' but don\'t have the space for a 20-foot tree, \'Winter Flame\' is essentially its compact, more manageable cousin.\n\nSpring: Delicate leaves emerge a soft, bright chartreuse-green, often edged with subtle pink or orange tones on the newer growth.\n\nSummer: The foliage matures into a deeper, clean grass-green that handles summer heat remarkably well for a coral-bark variety.\n\nAutumn: The leaves turn a brilliant, fiery blend of bright yellow, orange, and soft red.\n\nWinter: Once the leaves drop, the magic happens. The young twigs and branches intensify into a shockingly vivid coral-pink to neon orange-red, creating a striking \"flame\" effect against gray winter landscapes or snow.\n\nSize & Habit: Compact, dense, and upright. Reaches about 6 to 8 feet tall and 4 to 5 feet wide over 10 years.\nLight: Prefers dappled shade or morning sun with afternoon protection. Too much harsh afternoon sun can scorch the delicate leaves; too much dense shade will dull the winter bark color.\nSoil & Water: Moist, rich, well-draining soil. It hates \"wet feet\" (standing water), so excellent drainage is a must. Mulch well to keep roots cool.\n\nCommon Name: \'Winter Flame\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Full sun/part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 6\' to 8\' tall and 4\' to 5\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 6\"- 8\" tall.', '[\"Winter Interest\",\"Dramatic Color\",\"Fall Color\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Visual Interest\",\"Winter Garden\",\"Color Contrast\",\"Compact Growth\",\"Dwarf Tree\",\"Bright Colors\",\"Asian Garden\",\"Patio Garden\",\"Low Maintenance\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 2, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:17', '2026-06-24 16:09:17'),
