(360, 'Dwarf Japanese Maple \'Ryuzu\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Dragons Head Pink Green Leaves---Beautiful!!', 'dwarf-japanese-maple-ryuzu-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-dragons-head-pink-green-leaves-beautiful', 'ETSY-0088', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/12c730/6058030026/il_fullxfull.6058030026_g6wo.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 6\"- 8\" tall. This amazing hidden gem for small gardens, containers, and bonsai enthusiasts. Its name translates to \"Dragon Head,\" which hints at its uniquely rugged, sculptural habit. If you are looking for a tree that packs maximum character into a minimal footprint, this dwarf variety is a fantastic choice. What makes \'Ryuzu\' stand out is how its dense, tightly clustered foliage shifts drastically through the seasons. Because it naturally stays small and develops a rugged, ancient look quite quickly, \'Ryuzu\' is highly prized for bonsai culture and rock gardens. It is also an excellent choice for a patio container specimen or as an accent plant near an entryway where you can appreciate its intricate texture up close.\n\nSpring: Leaves emerge a bright, yellowish-green, often with delicate, faint red margins along the edges.\n\nSummer: The foliage matures into a crisp, rich kelly green. The leaves are small, deeply divided, and grow closely together along short, stocky branches.\n\nAutumn: This is its showstopper moment. The canopy erupts into a brilliant mix of fiery oranges, glowing yellows, and deep crimson reds.\n\nSize & Growth: A true dwarf. It grows slowly, typically reaching only 4 to 6 feet tall and wide after 10 to 15 years. It naturally forms a tight, rounded, shrub-like mound.\n\nTexture: Because the nodes (the spaces between leaves) are incredibly short, the tree has a highly compact, tufted texture. The older bark develops a rough, aged look relatively early in its life.\n\nSunlight: Thrives in partial shade. It loves morning sun but needs protection from harsh, direct afternoon heat to keep its delicate leaf tips from scorching.\n\nSoil: Requires moist, organically rich, and sharply well-draining soil. Like most Japanese maples, it hates sitting in soggy, compacted dirt.\n\nCommon Name: \'Ryuzu\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum \nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Full sun/part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 4\' to 6\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 6\"- 8\" tall.', '[\"Dwarf Tree\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Brilliant Fall Color\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Bonsai Tree\",\"Small Garden Space\",\"Container Garden\",\"Woodland Grden\",\"Asian Garden\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Interesting Leaves\",\"Compact Tree\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:19', '2026-06-24 16:09:19'),
(361, 'Japanese Maple \'Orion\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Dwarf Reddish Brown Leaves---Beautiful!!', 'japanese-maple-orion-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-dwarf-reddish-brown-leaves-beautiful', 'ETSY-0089', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/c3c580/5418241909/il_fullxfull.5418241909_onh9.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 10\"- 12\" tall. This cultivar is a highly prized dwarf variety, especially famous for its striking color contrast and compact, mounding habit. It is an excellent choice for small gardens, containers, or rock gardens.\n\nColor Show: What makes \'Orion\' unique is its multi-toned foliage. The older, mature leaves turn a deep maroon or dark purple-bronze, while the continuous new flushes of growth emerge a bright, vibrant crimson-red. This creates a beautiful \"two-tone\" layering effect throughout the summer. In autumn, the entire tree turns a brilliant, solid red.\n\nSize & Shape: It is a slow-growing dwarf cultivar. It typically reaches only 3 to 4 feet tall and slightly wider over 10 years, forming a dense, dense globose (rounded) mound.\n\nLeaves: The foliage is deeply divided and delicate, giving it a soft, textured appearance despite its tough nature.\n\nSunlight: Morning sun with afternoon shade is ideal. In hot climates, harsh afternoon sun can scorch the delicate leaf tips.\nSoil: Prefers moist, rich, well-draining soil. It dislikes heavy, soggy clay which can lead to root rot.\nWatering: Requires regular watering, especially during hot summer stretches. Keep the soil evenly damp but not waterlogged.\n\nCommon Name: \'Orion\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Full sun/part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 3\' to 4\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 10\"- 12\" tall.', '[\"Japanese Maple\",\"Dwarf Tree\",\"Red Leaves\",\"Orange Leaves\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Container Plant\",\"Small Space\",\"Small Garden\",\"Patio Plant\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Fall Color\",\"Compact Plant\",\"Lacy Leaves\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:19', '2026-06-24 16:09:19'),
(362, 'Japanese Maple \'Peve Starfish\' Acer palmatum Live Tree Dwarf Grafted Downward Curled Red/Maroon Leaves---Unique!!', 'japanese-maple-peve-starfish-acer-palmatum-live-tree-dwarf-grafted-downward-curled-redmaroon-leaves-unique', 'ETSY-0090', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/af6c52/5383295854/il_fullxfull.5383295854_ns9p.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 10\"- 12\" tall. This is a truly unique and highly prized dwarf variety! This is a fascinating, relatively rare dwarf cultivar known for its highly unique leaf structure. Discovered and named by Piet Vergelt in the Netherlands, its defining trait is the way its long, symmetrical leaf lobes curl downwards at the edges, strongly mimicking the shape of a starfish.   \n\nThe tree offers beautiful visual transitions throughout the growing season: \nSpring: Leaf-out emerges a striking, vibrant bright red.  \nSummer: The foliage matures into a deeper, rich burgundy or dark maroon.  \nFall: It finishes the year with a spectacular display of bright crimson/scarlet red.\n\nForm: Upright, compact, and somewhat narrow or columnar compared to spreading maples.  Growth Rate: Moderate to slow dwarf growth (averaging 6 to 9 inches a year).  \nMature Size: Reaches roughly 6 to 8 feet tall and 3 to 5 feet wide over a 10-to-20-year period. Because it stays compact, it is absolutely perfect for small garden beds, accent points, or large patio containers.\n\"If you plant \'Peve Starfish\' in the ground, avoid heavy fertilizers, as too much nitrogen can cause it to lose its compact shape and vibrant coloring. A simple layer of organic mulch around the base (keeping it a few inches away from the direct bark of the trunk) is usually all it needs to maintain moisture and soil health.\"\n\nSun Exposure: It does best in morning sun with afternoon shade, or all-day dappled/filtered sunlight. Protecting it from harsh, intense late-afternoon summer sun prevents the delicate leaf tips from scorching.  \n\nSoil & Water: Prefers rich, moist, but well-draining soil with a slightly acidic to neutral pH (5.0 to 7.0). Like most Japanese maples, its biggest enemy is waterlogged, soggy soil, which can cause root rot.\n\nCommon Name: \'Peve Starfish\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Full sun/part sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 6\'-8\' tall and 3\'-5\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 10\"- 12\" tall.', '[\"Unique Leaves\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Spring Color\",\"Fall Color\",\"Dwarf Tree\",\"Small Space\",\"Specimen Tree\",\"Japanese Garden\",\"Curled Leaves\",\"Hard To Find\",\"Patio Garden\",\"Asian Garden\",\"Small Tree\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 4, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:19', '2026-06-24 16:09:19'),
(363, 'Scotch Pine \'KBN Gold\' Pinus sylvestris Live Grafted Plant Yellow Winter Foliage Color---Beautiful!!', 'scotch-pine-kbn-gold-pinus-sylvestris-live-grafted-plant-yellow-winter-foliage-color-beautiful', 'ETSY-0091', 'simple', 16, NULL, 'Specialty Evergreens', 29.95, NULL, 17.97, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/a892a8/8049654519/il_fullxfull.8049654519_rpx4.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live  grafted plants that is 6\"- 8\" tall! This is a great smaller sized Pine that delivers visual interest all year! More sun gives you bright golden needles while more shade gives you more green. In Spring and Summer, the needles are  dark green! In Fall, the foliage starts changing and by Winter, it has turned into a gorgeous shade of yellow that holds through the season! It doesn\'t grow very big, and is low spreading so it\'s a great choice for a small garden space! A perfect plant to add a punch of color!!\n\n\nCommon Name: \'KBN Gold\' Scotch Pine\nBotanical Name: Pinus sylvestris\nHardiness Zones: 4 - 8\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Full sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 2\' to 3\' tall and 2\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Evergreen', '1 live grafted plants that is 6\"- 8\" tall! This is a great smaller sized Pine that delivers visual interest all year! More sun gives you bright golden needles while more shade gives you more green.', '[\"Evergreen Shrub\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Showy Foliage\",\"Small Garden Space\",\"Container Garden\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Brilliant Fall Color\",\"Dwarf Conifer\",\"Yellow Winter Color\",\"No Pruning Needed\",\"Color Contrast\",\"Specimen Plant\",\"Low Spreading\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:19', '2026-06-24 16:09:19'),
(364, 'Lilac \'Old Glory\' Syringa hyacinthiflora Live Plant Flowering Shrub Fragrant Bluish Purple Flowers---Gorgeous!!', 'lilac-old-glory-syringa-hyacinthiflora-live-plant-flowering-shrub-fragrant-bluish-purple-flowers-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0092', 'simple', 17, NULL, 'Lilacs', 25.45, NULL, 15.27, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/c96976/6510485875/il_fullxfull.6510485875_7t3r.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live plant that is 5\"- 6\" tall and growing! This Lilac is considered a Southern variety since it holds up to heat and humidity! In Spring, it is covered with rounded panicles of single bluish purple flowers that are fragrant! Perfect to use as an informal flowering hedge and all of your pollinators will love it!!\n\n\nCommon Name: \'Old Glory\' Lilac\nBotanical Name: Syringa hyacinthiflora\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 8\nBloom Time: Spring\nSunlight: Full sun/part sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 8\' to 10\' tall and 10\' to 12\' wide\nBloom Color: Bluish purple\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live plant that is 5\"- 6\" tall and growing! This Lilac is considered a Southern variety since it holds up to heat and humidity! In Spring, it is covered with rounded panicles of single bluish purple flowers that are fr...', '[\"Fragrant Flowers\",\"Bee Friendly\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Early Flowers\",\"Cut Flowers\",\"Hummingbirds Love\",\"Attracts Pollinators\",\"Mildew Resistant\",\"Deer Resistant\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Flowering Hedge\",\"Privacy Screen\",\"Mixed Shrub Border\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 6, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:20', '2026-06-24 16:09:20'),
(365, 'Beni Hagoromo Japanese Maple Grafted Tree, Red Feathery Leaves---Gorgeous!!', 'beni-hagoromo-japanese-maple-grafted-tree-red-feathery-leaves-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0093', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/8fadce/5871099005/il_fullxfull.5871099005_7jv5.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 10\" - 12\" tall. This beautiful variety is one of the most unique and collectible Japanese maples you can find. Its name beautifully translates to \"Red Feathered Robe,\" which perfectly describes its highly unusual, deeply divided foliage.\nUnlike standard maples with webbed leaves, this cultivar features heavily serrated, narrow lobes that fuse right at the petiole (leaf stem), giving the tree a distinctly feathery, fern-like texture.\n\nSpring: Leaves emerge in a striking, deep reddish-maroon to brick-red.\n\nSummer: The foliage matures into a unique blend of red-green or smoky bronze, depending on how much sun it gets.\n\nFall: The tree puts on a spectacular grand finale with vibrant shades of bright orange and fiery red.\n\nSize & Shape: It is a slow-growing, small tree or large shrub, typically reaching 8 to 12 feet tall and about 5 to 6 feet wide over 10 to 15 years. It maintains a compact, upright, and somewhat bushy habit, making it perfect for smaller gardens, containers, or courtyards.\n\nSunlight: It thrives best in morning sun and afternoon shade (dappled light is ideal). In hotter climates, hot afternoon sun can scorch its delicate, finely cut leaves.\n\nSoil: Like most Japanese maples, it demands well-draining, moist, and slightly acidic soil. It absolutely hates having \"wet feet\" (sitting in stagnant water).\n\nCommon Name: \'Beni Hagoromo\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Full sun/part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 8\' to 12\' tall and 5\' to 6\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 10\" - 12\" tall.', '[\"Japanese Maple\",\"Bonsai Plant\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Dramatic Fall Color\",\"Unique Leaf Shape\",\"Feather Leaf\",\"Graceful Shape\",\"Upright Growth\",\"Medium Size Tree\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Urban Garden\",\"Woodland Garden\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 2, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:20', '2026-06-24 16:09:20'),
(366, 'Japanese Maple \'Phantom Flame\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Rare Reticulated Red Purple Tipped Leaves---Gorgeous!!', 'japanese-maple-phantom-flame-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-rare-reticulated-red-purple-tipped-leaves-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0094', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/d85ea7/5407613852/il_fullxfull.5407613852_jew7.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live plant that is 10\"-12\" tall. This hard to find grafted variety is simply breathtaking! This cultivar is an absolute showstopper of a collector\'s tree. It belongs to the \"reticulated\" family of Japanese maples, which means its leaves feature highly visible, contrasting veins that look almost like a stained-glass window. What makes \'Phantom Flame\' truly remarkable is its dynamic, dramatic color transformation across the seasons.\n\nSpring: The show begins with a burst of bright chartreuse to lime-green leaves. Notice how the dark green veins create a web-like pattern across the tissue, while the deeply divided lobes are sharply outlined with a striking reddish-purple border.\n\nSummer: The bright chartreuse softens into deeper greens, but the heavily etched vein patterns remain prominent, giving the foliage a rich, textured depth during the heat of the year.\n\nAutumn: True to its name, the tree finishes the season with a fiery display of brilliant oranges and radiant reds.\n\nLight: While it needs some sunlight to bring out those intense spring and fall colors, hot afternoon sun can easily scorch the delicate, variegated leaf tissues. Filtered light or dappled shade is perfect.\n\nSoil: Like most Japanese maples, it thrives in moist, organically rich, slightly acidic soil that drains exceptionally well. They hate having \"wet feet\" (standing water).\n\nCommon Name: \'Phantom Flame\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Part sun/part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 6\' - 8\' tall and 5\' to 6\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live plant that is 10\"-12\" tall.', '[\"Medium Size Tree\",\"Reticulated Leaves\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Spring Color\",\"Fall Color\",\"Asian Garden\",\"Accent Plant\",\"Bonsai Tree\",\"Container Garden\",\"Container Plant\",\"Rare Tree\",\"Interesting Leaves\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 2, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:20', '2026-06-24 16:09:20'),
(367, 'Japanese Maple \'Kawahara Rose\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Pink Red Green Leaves---Gorgeous!!', 'japanese-maple-kawahara-rose-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-pink-red-green-leaves-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0095', 'simple', 9, NULL, 'Roses', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/257999/6108314153/il_fullxfull.6108314153_ggsc.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 10\"- 12\" tall. This variety gives you a little surprise in Summer! This is a rare, highly sought-after collector\'s cultivar known for its spectacular shifting colors and distinct leaf texture.\n\nStriking Variegation: What makes \'Kawahara Rose\' stand out is its intricate, multi-colored foliage. The leaves feature a slightly crinkled, deeply divided structure with distinct serrated edges.\nThe Seasonal Color Shift:\n\nSpring: Leaves emerge with brilliant, intense shades of rose-pink, coral, and soft orange.\n\nSummer: The foliage transitions to a beautiful, frosted matte green or light chartreuse in the center, heavily margined and mottled with creamy pink and hot rose highlights.\n\nAutumn: The tree puts on a final show, turning deep, fiery shades of orange and crimson.\n\nThe Sun Balance: Like many highly variegated Japanese maples, \'Kawahara Rose\' needs protection from the harshest afternoon sun. Too much direct, scorching summer heat will burn the delicate pink margins, while too much dense shade will cause the vibrant colors to fade back to a dull green.\nLight: Morning sun with dappled afternoon shade is perfect. If you live in a hot southern climate, lean heavily toward filtered shade.\nSoil: It thrives in rich, consistently moist, well-draining soil. It prefers a slightly acidic pH. Avoid heavy, waterlogged clay, which can invite root rot.\nWatering: Water regularly, especially during its first few growing seasons to establish a deep root system. Mulch around the base (keeping it a couple of inches away from the trunk) to help retain soil moisture and keep the roots cool.\nPruning: Requires very little maintenance. Limit pruning to the late winter or early spring dormant period, only removing dead, damaged, or crossing branches to maintain its elegant, natural shape.\n\nCommon Name: \'Kawahara Rose\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum dissectum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Full sun/part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 6 \' -8\' tall and 4\' - 6\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 10\"- 12\" tall.', '[\"Fall Color\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Small Garden Space\",\"Rock Garden\",\"Fairy Garden Tree\",\"Brilliant Leaf Color\",\"Small Tree\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Container Garden\",\"Color Contrast\",\"Specimen Tree\",\"Bright Colors\",\"Upright Growing\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:20', '2026-06-24 16:09:20'),
(368, 'Japanese Maple \'Sekka Yatsubusa\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Rare Unique Leaves---Hard To Find!!', 'japanese-maple-sekka-yatsubusa-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-rare-unique-leaves-hard-to-find', 'ETSY-0096', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/fe72c3/6882165165/il_fullxfull.6882165165_k7ck.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 8\" - 10\" tall. This beautiful variety is rare and is an exceptional, highly sought-after dwarf cultivar of the Japanese Maple (Acer palmatum). The name itself tells its story: in Japanese gardening terms, \"Yatsubusa\" translates to \"eight tassels\" or \"dwarf clump,\" signaling its ultra-compact, multi-budded growth habit, while \"Sekka\" refers to its unique crested or fan-like branch structure. It is an incredibly architectural plant, making it a prized choice for collectors, small rock gardens, containers, and bonsai enthusiasts.\n\nFoliage & Texture: The tiny, deeply divided 5-lobed leaves are tightly packed along short stems. This extreme density gives the tree a heavily tufted, cloud-like appearance.\n\nSpring: Leaves emerge with striking orange, red, or bronze margins on bright yellow-green centers.\nSummer: The foliage matures into a rich, deep emerald green.\nAutumn: It puts on a brilliant late-season show, turning vibrant shades of golden-yellow, bright orange, and crimson red.\n\nSize & Silhouette: This is a very slow-growing cultivar. It typically gains only 2 to 4 inches of growth per year, ultimately reaching around 4 to 6 feet tall and 3 to 4 feet wide after 10 to 15 years. Its natural habit is upright and vase-shaped, but beautifully irregular.\n\nSunlight: Morning sun with afternoon shade (dappled light is perfect to protect the tiny leaves from scorching).\nSoil: Moist, rich, organic, and exceptionally well-drained. Like most maples, it hates sitting in soggy soil.\nWatering: Regular, consistent watering. Container-grown specimens will require closer monitoring to ensure they don\'t dry out completely.\n\nCommon Name: \'Sekka Yatsubusa\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Full sun/part sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 4\' to 6\' tall and 3\' to 4\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 8\" - 10\" tall.', '[\"Japanese Maples\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Small Garden Space\",\"Patio Garden\",\"Woodland Garden\",\"Asian Garden\",\"Rare Tree\",\"Dwarf Tree\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Narrow Leaves\",\"Bright Fall Color\",\"Hard To Find Tree\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 3, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:20', '2026-06-24 16:09:20'),
(369, 'Japanese Maple \'Iro Iro\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Variegated Pink Cream Green Leaves---Beautiful!!', 'japanese-maple-iro-iro-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-variegated-pink-cream-green-leaves-beautiful', 'ETSY-0097', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/c2ff49/6169087652/il_fullxfull.6169087652_i27v.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 8\" - 12\" tall. This is such a unique cultivar! This cultivar is a highly sought-after, rare cultivar known for its striking, multi-colored foliage. The name literally translates from Japanese to \"various colors,\" which perfectly describes the dynamic shifting palette this tree puts on display throughout the growing season. If you are looking to add an eye-catching collector\'s plant with season-long interest to a semi-shaded spot, this cultivar is a fantastic choice.\n\nFoliage & Color Shifts: In spring, the deeply divided leaves emerge with bright, creamy-white variegation heavily flushed with soft pink or rose margins. As summer approaches, the pink fades, leaving a stark, clean contrast of deep green and white. By autumn, it puts on a final show with vibrant hues of orange and red.\n\nSize & Growth Habit: It typically grows into a small, upright, densely branched tree or large shrub. Expect it to reach around 6 to 8 feet tall and wide over a 10-year period, making it excellent for smaller gardens, containers, or courtyards.\n\nLight Requirements: Like many variegated maples, \'Iro iro\' prefers morning sun and afternoon shade. Too much direct, harsh afternoon sun can scorch the delicate white parts of the leaves, while too much dense shade can cause the variegation to fade back to solid green.\n\nSoil: Well-draining, moist, slightly acidic, and rich in organic matter\nWatering: Regular, consistent watering (do not let it completely dry out, but avoid soggy roots)\nMulch: Apply a layer of mulch around the base to keep the root system cool and retain moisture\n\nCommon Name: \'Iro Iro\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum \nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Full sun/part sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 6\' to 8\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 8\" - 12\" tall.', '[\"Variegated Leaves\",\"Understory Tree\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Brilliant Fall Color\",\"Reticulated Leaves\",\"Visual Interest\",\"Interesting Leaves\",\"Adds Texture\",\"Woodland Garden\",\"Asian Garden\",\"Japanese Maple\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 2, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:21', '2026-06-24 16:09:21'),
(370, 'Mountain Laurel \'Elf\' Kalmia latifolia Evergreen Plant Flowering Shrub Pink Buds to Near-White Flowers---Gorgeous!!', 'mountain-laurel-elf-kalmia-latifolia-evergreen-plant-flowering-shrub-pink-buds-to-near-white-flowers-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0098', 'simple', 7, NULL, 'Flowering Shrubs', 34.20, NULL, 20.52, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/77ed76/8095100251/il_fullxfull.8095100251_tnch.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live plant that is 6\" - 8\" tall! Mountain Laurels are hard to find!! In late Spring/early Summer, it has bright pink buds that open up into near-white flowers! The stamens are very visible and make a unique star shaped pattern inside the flower! It has a long bloom time, so you can enjoy gorgeous flowers for quite a while! It\'s semi-dwarf size makes it a great choice for containers too!!\n\nCommon Name: \'Elf\' Dwarf Mountain Laurel\nBotanical Name: Kalmia latifolia\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: Late Spring/early Summer \nSunlight: Morning sun, afternoon shade is best\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 2\' - 3\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: Near-White\nEvergreen or Deciduous: Evergreen', '1 live plant that is 6\" - 8\" tall! Mountain Laurels are hard to find!! In late Spring/early Summer, it has bright pink buds that open up into near-white flowers! The stamens are very visible and make a unique star shaped...', '[\"Easy To Grow\",\"Long Bloom Time\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Bee Friendly\",\"Attracts Pollinators\",\"Hard To Find Shrub\",\"Evergreen Shrub\",\"Container Plant\",\"Small Garden Space\",\"Abundant Flowers\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Woodland Garden\",\"Compact And Bushy\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 7, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:21', '2026-06-24 16:09:21'),
(371, 'Japanese Maple \'Shidava Gold\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Rare Dwarf Pea Green Stems Year Round---Hard To Find!!', 'japanese-maple-shidava-gold-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-rare-dwarf-pea-green-stems-year-round-hard-to-find', 'ETSY-0099', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/a9c62f/6151144713/il_fullxfull.6151144713_18dn.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 8\"- 12\" tall. A rare and hard to find green bark dwarf cultivar! This cultivar is a highly sought-after, semi-dwarf cultivar loved for its striking color transformations and year-round visual appeal. Originating as a \"witches\' broom\" mutation on the larger \'Aoyagi\' cultivar in Australia, it offers all the best features of its parent tree but in a much tighter, more compact form.  Because of its smaller stature and slow-to-moderate growth rate, it is also a popular candidate for bonsai enthusiasts who want to showcase the brilliant green winter bark.\n\nFour-Season Color Shifts:\nSpring: Leaves emerge as a vibrant, glowing yellow-green or chartreuse.\nSummer: The foliage matures into a crisp, bright lime-green.\nFall: The tree puts on a spectacular final show, turning a deep, rich golden-yellow to soft orange.\nWinter: Once the leaves drop, the tree remains a focal point due to its intense, bright pea-green bark and stems.\n\nSize & Habit: It features a dense, upright, vase-shaped growth habit. It typically matures to around 6 to 10 feet tall and 5 to 6 feet wide over 10 to 15 years, making it an excellent choice for smaller yards, rock gardens, or large patio containers.\n\nSun Exposure: Morning sun with afternoon shade is ideal. Full afternoon sun can cause the leaf tips to scorch or \"crinkle.\"\nWatering: Regular, consistent watering. It needs extra moisture during hot summer spells, especially if grown in a pot.\nSoil Preference: Rich, moist, well-draining, and slightly acidic soil. Avoid heavy, waterlogged clay.\nMaintenance: Very low. Pruning is rarely needed except to remove dead wood, which should only be done in late winter while the tree is dormant.\n\nCommon Name: \'Shidava Gold\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum \nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Part sun/part sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 6\' to 10\' tall and 5\' to 6\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 8\"- 12\" tall.', '[\"Year Round Color\",\"Rare Tree\",\"Small Garden Space\",\"Bonsai Tree\",\"Patio Garden\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Visual Interest\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Dwarf Tree\",\"Woodland Garden\",\"Flashy Foliage\",\"Compact Tree\",\"Interesting Bark\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 4, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:21', '2026-06-24 16:09:21');
