(372, 'Fukinagashi Japanese Maple Grafted Tree, Thread Leaf Acer Palmatum', 'fukinagashi-japanese-maple-grafted-tree-thread-leaf-acer-palmatum', 'ETSY-0100', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/6f2c81/5431732429/il_fullxfull.5431732429_fqgn.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n***WE DO NOT SHIP TO PO BOXES***\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 10\" - 12\" tall. This is a thread leaf variety that packs a visual punch! This is a stunning, relatively rare dwarf cultivar of the Japanese Maple family (Acer palmatum). It belongs to the linearilobum group, often referred to as \"strap-leaf\" or \"bamboo-leaf\" maples because their leaf lobes are incredibly narrow and delicate.  If you are a collector or looking for a distinct visual anchor for a small garden space, this tree is a showstopper.\n\nThe Foliage: The strap-like leaves are highly irregular. Some emerge incredibly thin, almost like threads, while others are slightly wider. They tend to curl subtly, giving the tree a slightly wild, texturized look that lives up to its \"wind-swept\" name.\nColor Transformation: \nSpring/Summer: Depending on the exact lineage and sun exposure, they emerge with deep burgundy tones or soft greens. By mid-summer, they mature into a handsome grayish-green or bright lime green. A second flush of growth later in the season often brings striking peach, copper, or apricot-colored leaves at the tips. \nFall: The foliage transitions into a brilliant, fiery palette ranging from bright yellows to deep crimson reds. \nThe Bark: Fukinagashi features distinct dark purple to almost-black twigs and bark. This dark skeleton creates a gorgeous, high-contrast backdrop that makes the lighter summer foliage visually pop. \nSize & Shape: This is a true dwarf variety. It has a compact, upright growth habit, typically reaching only 6 to 7 feet tall and 4 to 5 feet wide after 10 years. Because of its small footprint and slower growth rate, it is an absolute dream for container gardening or tight patio spaces.\n\nSun Exposure: Dappled sun to partial shade (Protect from harsh afternoon sun)\nWatering: Even moisture; regular watering without waterlogging\n\nCommon Name: \'Fukinagashi\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Full sun/part sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 6\' to 7\' tall and 4\' to 5\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 10\" - 12\" tall.', '[\"Thread Leaf\",\"Strap Leaf\",\"Slow Growing\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Fall Color\",\"Small Space\",\"Japanese Garden\",\"Patio Garden\",\"City Garden\",\"Compact Growth\",\"Upright Growth\",\"Hard To Find\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 2, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:22', '2026-06-24 16:09:22'),
(373, 'Weigela florida \'Red Prince\' Starter Plant 2 1/2\" Pot  Red Funnel Shaped Flowers---Gorgeous!!', 'weigela-florida-red-prince-starter-plant-2-12-pot-red-funnel-shaped-flowers-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0101', 'simple', 7, NULL, 'Flowering Shrubs', 16.85, NULL, 10.11, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/8c6488/4002399647/il_fullxfull.4002399647_lu1d.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live starter plant that is 3\" - 5\" tall and multi-branched. This beautiful variety has dark green leaves and red flowers in late Spring to early Summer that are tubular shaped...Hummingbirds and butterflies love them!! It grows in a compact mounding shape, so these work great as a low hedge. These can be used in containers too!!\n\nCommon Name: \'Red Prince\' Weigela\nBotanical Name: Weigela florida\nHardiness Zones: 4 - 8\nBloom Time: Spring to early Summer\nSunlight: Full sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 5\' - 6\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: Red\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live starter plant that is 3\" - 5\" tall and multi-branched.', '[\"Low Maintenance\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Easy Care\",\"Attracts Butterflies\",\"Urban Garden\",\"Pollinators Love\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Reblooming Shrub\",\"Flowering Hedge\",\"Specimen Plant\",\"Dense Growth\",\"Hummingbirds Love\",\"Deer Resistant\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 3, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:22', '2026-06-24 16:09:22'),
