(382, 'Knockout Rose \'Peachy\' Starter Plant Shell Pink/Yellow Center Flowers---Beautiful!!', 'knockout-rose-peachy-starter-plant-shell-pinkyellow-center-flowers-beautiful', 'ETSY-0110', 'simple', 9, NULL, 'Roses', 25.45, NULL, 15.27, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/0d7458/8049556143/il_fullxfull.8049556143_2bic.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live starter plant that is 3\" - 6\" tall and growing quickly in a quart pot! This variety is a highly disease-resistant, low maintenance shrub rose. It has shell pink with yellow center flowers that bloom continuously from spring until frost and don\'t require deadheading!!\n\nCommon Name: \'Peachy\'  Knockout Rose\nBotanical Name: Rosa \'Radgor\' PP 25,628\nHardiness Zones: 4 - 10\nBloom Time: Spring, Summer, Fall\nSunlight: Full sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 3\' to 4\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: Pink with yellow center\nEvergreen or Deciduous: Deciduous', '1 live starter plant that is 3\" - 6\" tall and growing quickly in a quart pot! This variety is a highly disease-resistant, low maintenance shrub rose.', '[\"Shrub Rose\",\"Long Bloom Time\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Cut Flowers\",\"Container Garden\",\"Garden Border\",\"Flowering Hedge\",\"Low Hedge\",\"Bushy Rose\",\"Fast Growing\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Self Deadheading\",\"Disease Resistant\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 4, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:24', '2026-06-24 16:09:24'),
(383, 'Hydrangea \'Pee Gee\' Live Starter Plant Flowering Shrub White Panicle Flowers--Beautiful!!', 'hydrangea-pee-gee-live-starter-plant-flowering-shrub-white-panicle-flowers-beautiful', 'ETSY-0111', 'simple', 10, NULL, 'Hydrangeas', 16.85, NULL, 10.11, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/1628c0/3966970065/il_fullxfull.3966970065_aif3.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live starter plant that is 3\" - 5\" tall and growing! This beautiful variety can be grown as a tree or a shrub and produces an abundance of showy white flower panicles in mid Summer. As the flowers age, they turn pink to bronze before finally turning brown. In Fall, the leaves turn bronze for even more visual interest! These are great to use as an informal and beautiful hedge due to how wide it grows!\n\nCommon Name: \'Pee Gee\' Hydrangea \nBotanical Name: Hydrangea paniculata grandiflora\nHardiness Zones: 3 - 8\nBloom Time: Mid Summer\nSunlight: Full sun/part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 8\' to 12\' tall and 8\' wide\nBloom Color: White\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live starter plant that is 3\" - 5\" tall and growing! This beautiful variety can be grown as a tree or a shrub and produces an abundance of showy white flower panicles in mid Summer.', '[\"Flower Panicles\",\"Urban Garden\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Full Sun\",\"Part Shade\",\"Fall Color\",\"Cut Flower\",\"Dried Flowers\",\"Curb Appeal\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Informal Hedge\",\"Sun Hydrangea\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 3, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:24', '2026-06-24 16:09:24'),
(384, 'Dwarf Hinoki Cypress \'Verdoni\' Chamaecyparis obtusa Live Starter Plant Evergreen Shrub Yellow Green---Beautiful!!', 'dwarf-hinoki-cypress-verdoni-chamaecyparis-obtusa-live-starter-plant-evergreen-shrub-yellow-green-beautiful', 'ETSY-0112', 'simple', 15, NULL, 'Evergreen Shrubs', 22.75, NULL, 13.65, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/eb4f04/6045193137/il_fullxfull.6045193137_9p2l.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live STARTER plant that is 3\"- 5\" tall. This dwarf evergreen shrub is definitely different! It grows in a kind of contorted shape which really adds visual interest! The new growth is yellow with hints of orange that matures to green! Its size makes it easy to use in small spaces and even in containers!!\n\nCommon Name: \'Verdoni\' Dwarf Hinoki Cypress\nBotanical Name: Chamaecyparis obtusa\nHardiness Zones: 4 - 8\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Full sun/part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 3\' to 8\' tall and 2\' to 3\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nEvergreen or Deciduous: Evergreen', '1 live STARTER plant that is 3\"- 5\" tall.', '[\"Hard To Find\",\"Rare Shrub\",\"Unique Foliage\",\"Rock Garden\",\"Container Garden\",\"Patio Plant\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Low Maintenence\",\"Asian Garden\",\"Winter Interest\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Shrub Border\",\"Low Hedge\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 9, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:24', '2026-06-24 16:09:24'),
(385, 'Butterfly Bush \'Silver Frost\' Buddleia davidii Live Plant Flowering Shrub Fragrant White Flowers---Lovely!!', 'butterfly-bush-silver-frost-buddleia-davidii-live-plant-flowering-shrub-fragrant-white-flowers-lovely', 'ETSY-0113', 'simple', 3, NULL, 'Perennials', 23.85, NULL, 14.31, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/7807b8/5060917375/il_fullxfull.5060917375_pwfx.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live plant that is 8\"-10\" tall. This beautiful variety has silvery gray foliage and fragrant white flowers in Summer that will attract all of your favorite pollinators! It has a more compact growth habit than other white varieties and the flowers are more upright too! Flowering continues all the way into Fall so you can enjoy it for a long time!!\n\nCommon Name: \'Silver Frost\' Butterfly Bush\nBotanical Name: Buddleia davidii\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: Summer to Fall\nSunlight: Full sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 4\' to 6\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: White\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Dies back to the ground in Winter and grows back in Spring', '1 live plant that is 8\"-10\" tall.', '[\"Fragrant Flowers\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Compact Habit\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Attracts Pollinators\",\"Attracts Bees\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Mass Planting\",\"Specimen Plant\",\"Deer Resistant\",\"Long Bloom Time\",\"Upright Flowers\",\"Hummingbirds Love\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 4, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:24', '2026-06-24 16:09:24'),
(386, 'Fashion Azalea Live Plant – Salmon-Orange to Red Blooms, Semi-Evergreen Shrub', 'fashion-azalea-live-plant-salmon-orange-to-red-blooms-semi-evergreen-shrub', 'ETSY-0114', 'simple', 15, NULL, 'Evergreen Shrubs', 23.30, NULL, 13.98, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/474ce9/7929884341/il_fullxfull.7929884341_mjme.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n\nThis listing is for 1 live plant that is 4\"- 6\" tall and multi-branched. This beautiful plant has so much to offer! It is an semi-evergreen (evergreen zone 8 to 10) ornamental shrub has medium to dark green leaves. In Spring, it explodes with gorgeous flowers that are salmon-orange to red that really stands out! It has an upright growth habit with a rounded shape and makes a great hedge! \n\nCommon Name: \"Fashion\" Azalea\nBotanical Name: Azalea x\nHardiness Zones: 6 - 10\nBloom Time: Spring, Summer\nSunlight: Morning sun and afternoon shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 2\' to 3\' tall and 3\' to 4\' wide\nBloom Color: Salmon-orange to Red\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Semi-Evergreen', '1 live plant that is 4\"- 6\" tall and multi-branched.', '[\"Low Maintenance\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Summer Flowers\",\"Compact\",\"Hedge\",\"Specimen\",\"Rebloomer\",\"Heat Resistant\",\"Drought Resistant\",\"Disease Resistant\",\"Fast Growing\",\"Bi-Color Flowers\",\"Vibrant Color\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 5, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:25', '2026-06-24 16:09:25'),
(387, 'Ji Jiao Japanese Maple Grafted Tree: Orange Coral Bark, All Season Interest', 'ji-jiao-japanese-maple-grafted-tree-orange-coral-bark-all-season-interest', 'ETSY-0115', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/9f9e12/6149952579/il_fullxfull.6149952579_90ma.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n***WE DO NOT SHIP TO PO BOXES***\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 10\"- 14\" tall. This beautiful orange coral bark cultivar is hard to find! The leaves on this variety are green, but that\'s not what makes it stand out in a crowd! The bark is bright orange to yellow orange depending on how much sun it gets! In Fall, the leaves change to gorgeous shades of oranges and reds! After the leaves drop, the show continues all Winter since the bark holds its color for great year round visual interest!!\n\nCommon Name: \'Ji Jiao\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum \nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Part sun/part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 10\' to 15\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 10\"- 14\" tall.', '[\"Rare Tree\",\"Hard To Find\",\"Unique Bark\",\"Brilliant Fall Color\",\"All Season Color\",\"Visual Interest\",\"Ornamental Tree\",\"Specimen Tree\",\"Small Garden Space\",\"Woodland Garden\",\"Contrasting Color\",\"Street Tree\",\"Excellent Fall Color\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:25', '2026-06-24 16:09:25'),
(388, 'Chantilly Lace Hydrangea Starter Plant: White to Pink Flowers, Flowering Shrub', 'chantilly-lace-hydrangea-starter-plant-white-to-pink-flowers-flowering-shrub', 'ETSY-0116', 'simple', 10, NULL, 'Hydrangeas', 16.85, NULL, 10.11, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/1f9896/4087722716/il_fullxfull.4087722716_392l.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n***WE DO NOT SHIP TO PO BOXES***\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live starter plant that is 3\"- 5\" tall and multi-branched. This absolutely gorgeous, sun variety blooms in Summer with bright white large airy cone shaped flower panicles that consists of small florets surrounded by larger flowers . It changes to soft pink as the flowers mature. The stems are very sturdy so the panicles don\'t flop. Definitely makes a  beautiful statement!\n\n\nCommon Name: \'Chantilly Lace\' Hydrangea\nBotanical Name: Hydrangea paniculata\nHardiness Zones: 3 - 9\nBloom Time: Summer\nSunlight: Full sun/part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 4\' to 6\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: White to soft pink\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live starter plant that is 3\"- 5\" tall and multi-branched.', '[\"Low Maintenance\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Summer Flowers\",\"Large Flowers\",\"Attracts Bees\",\"Attracts Butterflies\",\"Cut Flowers\",\"Fall Color\",\"Urban Garden\",\"Specimen Plant\",\"Mass Planting\",\"Dried Flowers\",\"Pollinator Friendly\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 6, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:25', '2026-06-24 16:09:25'),
