(390, 'Japanese Maple \'Dr. Seuss\' Acer palmatum Live Grafted Tree Rare Dwarf Yellow Green Variegated Leaves---Gorgeous!!', 'japanese-maple-dr-seuss-acer-palmatum-live-grafted-tree-rare-dwarf-yellow-green-variegated-leaves-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0118', 'simple', 14, NULL, 'Japanese Maples', 32.95, NULL, 19.77, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/c97619/6169850153/il_fullxfull.6169850153_qpyn.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live grafted tree that is 8\"- 10\" tall. This variegated dwarf cultivar is rare and hard to find! In Spring, the new leaves emerge green with yellow variegation on the edges! In Fall, the colors change to a brilliant display of orange and red! It\'s mature size makes it great to use in a container or a small garden space!!\n\nCommon Name: \'Dr. Seuss\' Japanese Maple\nBotanical Name: Acer palmatum \nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: N/A\nSunlight: Part sun/part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 8\' to 12\' tall and 5\' to 8\' wide\nBloom Color: N/A\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live grafted tree that is 8\"- 10\" tall.', '[\"Rare Tree\",\"Dwarf Tree\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Container Tree\",\"Patio Garden\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Small Garden Space\",\"Unique Leaves\",\"Dramatic Leaf Color\",\"Brilliant Fall Color\",\"Ornamental Tree\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Dense Growth\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:25', '2026-06-24 16:09:25'),
(391, 'Arizona Cypress Live Plant, Evergreen Pyramid Shaped Tree', 'arizona-cypress-live-plant-evergreen-pyramid-shaped-tree', 'ETSY-0119', 'simple', 16, NULL, 'Specialty Evergreens', 24.75, NULL, 14.85, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/28d45d/8001461266/il_fullxfull.8001461266_ghec.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live plant that are 6\"- 8\" tall and growing! This is a great evergreen tree! It grows in a pyramid shape and has gently arching branches! The beautiful gray-green to blue-green color holds all through Winter to add visual interest to an otherwise bare landscape! Sometime grown for Christmas trees!!\n\nCommon Name: Arizona Cypress\nBotanical Name: Cupressus arizonica\nHardiness Zones: 7 - 10\nBloom Time: N/A \nSunlight: Full sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 30\' to 40\' tall and 15\' to 25\' wide\nBloom Color: Small round cones\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Evergreen', '1 live plant that are 6\"- 8\" tall and growing! This is a great evergreen tree! It grows in a pyramid shape and has gently arching branches! The beautiful gray-green to blue-green color holds all through Winter to add vis...', '[\"Wildlife Habitat\",\"Low Maintenance\",\"Fast Growing\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Rock Garden\",\"Coastal Garden\",\"Drought Tolerant\",\"No Pruning Needed\",\"Courtyard Garden\",\"Evergreen\",\"Native\",\"Conifer\",\"Wind Break\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 2, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:25', '2026-06-24 16:09:25'),
