(393, 'Yellow Buckeye Aesculus flava Live Plant Yellow Flower Panicles---Fast Growing!!', 'yellow-buckeye-aesculus-flava-live-plant-yellow-flower-panicles-fast-growing', 'ETSY-0121', 'simple', 3, NULL, 'Perennials', 29.85, NULL, 17.91, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/b72697/6513227575/il_fullxfull.6513227575_kuvi.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live plant that is 18\"- 24\" tall and growing! If you are looking for a Buckeye that grows fast and tall, then this is the one! In late Spring/early Summer, it produces upright panicles of yellow flowers that turn into round fruit that contains 1-3 seeds! Due to its mature size, make sure to give it plenty of room!!\n\nCommon Name: Yellow Buckeye\nBotanical Name: Aesculus flava\nHardiness Zones: 4 - 8\nBloom Time: Spring/Summer \nSunlight: Full sun/part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 60\' to 75\' tall and 30\' to 50\' wide\nBloom Color: Yellow\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live plant that is 18\"- 24\" tall and growing! If you are looking for a Buckeye that grows fast and tall, then this is the one! In late Spring/early Summer, it produces upright panicles of yellow flowers that turn into...', '[\"Fast Growing Tree\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Native Tree\",\"Brilliant Fall Color\",\"Attractive Foliage\",\"Smooth Husk\",\"Shade Tree\",\"Specimen Tree\",\"Large Landscapes\",\"Wildlife Food Source\",\"Attracts Pollinators\",\"Hummingbirds Love\",\"Deer Resistant\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 2, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:26', '2026-06-24 16:09:26'),
(394, 'Charlet Purple Butterfly Bush \'Ile de France\' Live Flowering Shrub Fragrant Violet Flowers---Stunning!!', 'charlet-purple-butterfly-bush-ile-de-france-live-flowering-shrub-fragrant-violet-flowers-stunning', 'ETSY-0122', 'simple', 3, NULL, 'Perennials', 23.85, NULL, 14.31, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/fb6654/5628425822/il_fullxfull.5628425822_6e6h.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live plant that is 6\"- 8\" tall. If you love Butterfly Bush, this is a definite keeper! In Summer, it explodes with fragrant violet purple flower with yellow eye panicles that are pollinator magnets! It has grayish green foliage that adds even more visual interest! Great to use as cut flowers too!!\n\n\nCommon Name: \'Ile de France\' Charlet Purple Butterfly Bush\nBotanical Name: Buddleja davidii\nHardiness Zones: 5 - 9\nBloom Time: Summer\nSunlight: Full sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 5\' to 6\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: Purple\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live plant that is 6\"- 8\" tall.', '[\"Cut Flowers\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Pollinator Plant\",\"Hummingbirds Love\",\"Fragrant Flowers\",\"Nectar Rich\",\"Wildlife Habitat\",\"Fuzzy New Leaves\",\"Spreading Growth\",\"Upright Growth\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Informal Garden\",\"Low Maintenance\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 5, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:26', '2026-06-24 16:09:26'),
(395, 'Purple Formosa Azalea Live Plant – Purple-Pink Blooms', 'purple-formosa-azalea-live-plant-purple-pink-blooms', 'ETSY-0123', 'simple', 7, NULL, 'Flowering Shrubs', 23.30, NULL, 13.98, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/6628ab/7881963062/il_fullxfull.7881963062_a5zt.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live plant that is 5\"- 7\" tall and multi-branched. This beautiful plant has so much to offer! It is an semi-evergreen (evergreen zone 8 to 10) southern ornamental shrub has medium to dark green leaves. In Spring, it explodes with gorgeous flowers that are purple-pink to lavender that really stands out! It has an upright growth habit with a rounded shape and makes a great hedge! \n\nCommon Name: \"Purple Formosa\" Azalea\nBotanical Name: Azalea indica\nHardiness Zones: 7 - 10\nBloom Time: Spring, Summer\nSunlight: Morning sun and afternoon shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 6\' to 8\' tall and 4\' to 6\' wide\nBloom Color: Purple-pink to lavender\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Semi-Evergreen', '1 live plant that is 5\"- 7\" tall and multi-branched.', '[\"Low Maintenance\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Compact\",\"Hedge\",\"Specimen\",\"Rebloomer\",\"Heat Resistant\",\"Drought Resistant\",\"Disease Resistant\",\"Fast Growing\",\"Vibrant Color\",\"Spring Flowers\",\"Fuchsia Color\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 3, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:26', '2026-06-24 16:09:26'),
(396, 'Weigela florida \'Red Prince\' Live Plant Flowering Shrub Red Funnel Shaped Flowers---Gorgeous!!', 'weigela-florida-red-prince-live-plant-flowering-shrub-red-funnel-shaped-flowers-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0124', 'simple', 7, NULL, 'Flowering Shrubs', 20.45, NULL, 12.27, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/6947c1/3954738718/il_fullxfull.3954738718_qe4z.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live plant that is 8\" - 10\" tall and multi-branched. This beautiful variety has dark green leaves and red flowers in late Spring to early Summer that are tubular shaped...Hummingbirds and butterflies love them!! It grows in a compact mounding shape, so these work great as a low hedge. These can be used in containers too!!\n\nCommon Name: \'Red Prince\' Weigela\nBotanical Name: Weigela florida\nHardiness Zones: 4 - 8\nBloom Time: Spring to early Summer\nSunlight: Full sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 5\' - 6\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: Red\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live plant that is 8\" - 10\" tall and multi-branched.', '[\"Low Maintenance\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Easy Care\",\"Attracts Butterflies\",\"Urban Garden\",\"Pollinators Love\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Reblooming Shrub\",\"Flowering Hedge\",\"Specimen Plant\",\"Dense Growth\",\"Hummingbirds Love\",\"Deer Resistant\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:26', '2026-06-24 16:09:26');
