(397, 'Hydrangea paniculata \'Pee Gee\' Live Plant Flowering Shrub White Panicle Flowers--Beautiful!!', 'hydrangea-paniculata-pee-gee-live-plant-flowering-shrub-white-panicle-flowers-beautiful', 'ETSY-0125', 'simple', 10, NULL, 'Hydrangeas', 24.75, NULL, 14.85, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/2256b2/3919462230/il_fullxfull.3919462230_1m81.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n\nThis listing is for 1 live plant that is 8\" - 12\" tall and growing! This beautiful variety can be grown as a tree or a shrub and produces an abundance of showy white flower panicles in mid Summer. As the flowers age, they turn pink to bronze before finally turning brown. In Fall, the leaves turn bronze for even more visual interest! These are great to use as an informal and beautiful hedge due to how wide it grows!\n\nCommon Name: \'Pee Gee\' Hydrangea \nBotanical Name: Hydrangea paniculata grandiflora\nHardiness Zones: 3 - 8\nBloom Time: Mid Summer\nSunlight: Full sun/part shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 8\' to 12\' tall and 8\' wide\nBloom Color: White\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live plant that is 8\" - 12\" tall and growing! This beautiful variety can be grown as a tree or a shrub and produces an abundance of showy white flower panicles in mid Summer.', '[\"Flower Panicles\",\"Urban Garden\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Easy To Grow\",\"Full Sun\",\"Part Shade\",\"Fall Color\",\"Cut Flower\",\"Dried Flowers\",\"Curb Appeal\",\"Showy Flowers\",\"Informal Hedge\",\"Sun Hydrangea\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 6, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:27', '2026-06-24 16:09:27'),
(398, 'Forsythia \'Lynwood Gold\' Starter Plant 2 1/2\" Pot. Flowering Shrub Bright Yellow Spring Flowers---Gorgeous!!', 'forsythia-lynwood-gold-starter-plant-2-12-pot-flowering-shrub-bright-yellow-spring-flowers-gorgeous', 'ETSY-0126', 'simple', 3, NULL, 'Perennials', 16.85, NULL, 10.11, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/4c4ae8/4204052131/il_fullxfull.4204052131_lz2n.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n*** WE DO NOT SHIP TO PO BOXES***\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n***ITEMS ARE TAPED IN THE BOX FOR SECURE SHIPPING. PLEASE BE CAREFUL TO REMOVE TAPE FIRST BEFORE REMOVING PLANT(S)***\n\nThis listing is for 1 live starter plant that is 3\"- 5\" tall, well branched. This beautiful plant brings tons of color to your garden in Spring when it explodes with golden yellow flowers before any leaves emerge!! These are great to use as a flowering hedge or as a stand alone specimen plant!! It\'s a sure sign that Spring has arrived when these start to bloom!!\n\nCommon Name: \'Lynwood Gold\' Forsythia\nBotanical Name: Forsythia x intermedia\nHardiness Zones: 4 - 8\nBloom Time: Spring\nSunlight: Full sun\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 6\' to 9\' tall and wide\nBloom Color: Yellow\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Deciduous', '1 live starter plant that is 3\"- 5\" tall, well branched.', '[\"Low Maintenance\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Spring Flowers\",\"Mass Planting\",\"Early Spring Flowers\",\"Attracts Birds\",\"Cut Flowers\",\"Deer Resistant\",\"Erosion Control\",\"Pollinator Plant\",\"Specimen Plant\",\"Hedge Plant\",\"Showy Flowers\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 10, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:27', '2026-06-24 16:09:27'),
(399, 'Red Formosa Azalea Starter Plant – Magenta Fuchsia Blooms, 2 1/2\" Pot', 'red-formosa-azalea-starter-plant-magenta-fuchsia-blooms-2-12-pot', 'ETSY-0127', 'simple', 7, NULL, 'Flowering Shrubs', 17.25, NULL, 10.35, NULL, 'https://i.etsystatic.com/20088520/r/il/814165/7881943370/il_fullxfull.7881943370_fc7o.jpg', 'WE CANNOT SHIP TO THE FOLLOWING STATES DUE TO SHIPPING RESTRICTIONS: CALIFORNIA, OREGON, WASHINGTON, ARIZONA, ALASKA, HAWAII, IDAHO AND NEVADA\n**WE CANNOT SHIP TO P.O. BOXES!!**\nSECOND PICTURE IS A REPRESENTATION OF THE PLANT YOU WILL RECEIVE.\n\nThis listing is for 1 live starter plant that is 5\"- 8\" tall and multi-branched. This beautiful plant has so much to offer! It is an semi-evergreen (evergreen zone 8 to 10) southern ornamental shrub has medium to dark green leaves. In Spring, it explodes with gorgeous flowers that are magenta/fuchsia to red that really stands out! It has an upright growth habit with a rounded shape and makes a great hedge! \n\nCommon Name: \"Red Formosa\" Azalea\nBotanical Name: Azalea indica\nHardiness Zones: 7 - 10\nBloom Time: Spring, Summer\nSunlight: Morning sun and afternoon shade\nSoil Requirements: Moist, well drained soil\nMature Size: 6\' to 8\' tall and 4\' to 6\' wide\nBloom Color: Magenta/Fuchsia to Red\nDeciduous or Evergreen: Semi-Evergreen', '1 live starter plant that is 5\"- 8\" tall and multi-branched.', '[\"Low Maintenance\",\"Cottage Garden\",\"Compact\",\"Hedge\",\"Specimen\",\"Rebloomer\",\"Heat Resistant\",\"Drought Resistant\",\"Disease Resistant\",\"Fast Growing\",\"Vibrant Color\",\"Spring Flowers\",\"Fuchsia Color\"]', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 10, 5, 1, 0, 5, '2026-06-24 16:09:27', '2026-06-24 16:09:27');
